<HEAD>
<TITLE>Director of Projects and New Products - Frank J. Batavick</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H1>Management and Staff</H1>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
<IMG SRC="batavick.gif" ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE="10">
<BR>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Frank J. Batavick</I></H2>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Director of Projects and New Products</H3>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<HR>
<P>
Frank J. Batavick is the Director of Projects and New Products for the Agency for Instructional 
Technology, Bloomington, Indiana.  Mr. Batavick received his M.A. from the University of Maryland, 
College Park in Radio-TV-Film and has worked in instructional materials development for over 25 years.  
As a writer, producer, director, and executive producer, he has developed more than 300 videos for 
audiences ranging from pre-school to adult.  In recent years, he has produced programs for multi-media 
formats, including bar coded laser disc.  These videos have garnered more than 45 regional and national 
awards, including a Peabody, Cindys, Teles, and Golden CINES, and have been widely seen on PBS 
stations and distributed internationally through AIT's marketing effort.  Most of these products have been 
supported by extensive text resources for both teachers and students.</P>
<P>
Mr. Batavick has served as adjunct faculty/visiting lecturer at four colleges/universities in courses ranging 
from station management to the effects of the mass media.  In 1990 he received the Governor's Citation, 
State of Maryland, for outstanding service to education and technology.  In 1995 he received a 
distinguished achievement award from EdPress for a <A HREF="/journal/volume3/1batavick.htm">colloquium piece</A> he penned on violence in current 
CD-ROM titles.</P>
<P>
Some of the instructional projects in the last six years released by AIT's Product Development staff include: </P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c317.htm">Workplace Readiness</A>
<LI>Taxes and You: Understanding Taxes
<LI>Science for You
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c352.htm">Science is Elementary</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c275.htm">Applied Communication: Next Steps</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c358.htm">Head to Toe</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c372.htm">Mathemedia</A>
<LI>Communication 2000 (with South-Western Publishing)
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c368.htm">Economics at Work</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c370.htm">Looking from the Inside/Out</A>
<LI>Mathematics is Elementary.
</UL>
<P>
Current efforts are focused on Science Links, and integrated curriculum for 9th grade; Civics at Work for senior high school, and ADD: What It Is.  What It Isn't.  What to do.</P>
<P>
Batavick and staff have also worked on a host of professional development titles, including: </P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c347.htm">Schools of Thought I</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c350.htm">Schools of Thought II</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c312.htm">Every Child Can Succeed</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c366.htm">Managing the Disruptive Classroom: Strategies for Educators</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c371.htm">Families and Schools: Teaming for Success</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c386.htm">Respecting Diversity in the Classroom</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c385.htm">Before the Bell Rings: What Every Paraeducator Should Know</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c373.htm">The Road to School-to-Work: A Map for Implementation</A>
<LI><A HREF="/catalog/catpages/c389.htm">Education Under Fire</A>
</UL>
<P>
Frank Batavick may be reached via e-mail at <A HREF="MAILTO:batavick@ait.net">batavick@ait.net</A>.</P>

<HR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="/ait/astaff.htm">Return to Listing of AIT's Staff Members</A>
</P>

<A HREF="/AIT/aitcopy.htm">&copy; AIT</A>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
