<TITLE>TECHNOS Quarterly Biography - Bonnie Bracey</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="OOOOFF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>
<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<A HREF="/technos/atechnos.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/technos/tpress.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<H1 align=center>TECHNOS Quarterly</H1>
<H2 align=center>for Education and Technology</H2>
<HR>

<H1 align=center>Biography</H1>
<P><IMG SRC="/journal/bios/3gbracey.gif" align=left hpsace=15>
<B>Bonnie Bracey</B> taught fourth and fifth grades at Ashlawn Elementary School in Arlington, Virginia, and is now Teacher in Residence at Arlington Career Center. She is the only K-12 teacher representative on the Vice President's NII Advisory Council. Bracey, a 1992 Christa McAuliffe Educator, serves on the national advisory boards of The Lightspan Partnership, the George Lucas Educational Foundation, and TECHNOS Quarterly.</P><BR CLEAR=LEFT>

