<HEAD>
<TITLE>A Trick and Technology Sidebar</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/backgrnd.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="FF00FF" ALINK="FF0000">
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=40><IMG SRC="/images/bgspace.gif" BORDER=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0></TD><TD>

<A HREF="/ait/aait.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/aitlogo.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>
<A HREF="/technos/atechnos.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/technos/tpress.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 HSPACE=0></A>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>TECHNOS Quarterly</H1>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>For Education and Technology</H2>
<H3 ALIGN=RIGHT>Vol. 5, No. 2, Summer 1996</H3>
<HR>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><I>A Trick and Technology*</I></H1>
<H4 align=center><I>STORYBOARD SCRIPT</I></H4>
<BR>
<H3 ALIGN=RIGHT>Sidebar for <A HREF="/journal/volume5/2carter.htm"><I>Computers in the Classroom of the Future</I></A></H3>
<HR>
<P><SMALL>(*Inspired by the childrens book <I>Miss Nelson Is Missing</I> by Henry Allard and James Marshall (Boston: Houghton Mifflin Company, 1977)).</SMALL></P>

<BR>
<P><B>Frame 1: Girl on a computer phone</B>
<BR>
It is Monday and Lindsay has come to school early to get help from Ms. Nelson on a team project. She finds a substitute, Ms. Swamp. When Lindsay asks a question, Ms. Swamp replies: <I>Computers? Oh, dearie! I don't know much about those things</I>. Lindsey quietly calls a team member: <I>Charlotte, we have a problem</I>.</P>

<P><B>Frame 2: Two girls talking in the classroom</B>
<BR>
Lindsay and Charlotte watch for Sarah to arrive. Ms. Swamp reminds girls their project is due Friday and Ms. Foret's class is coming to see their presentation.</P>

<P>Ms. Swamp: <I>Dearies, Ms. Nelson will be out all week</I>.</P>

<P>Lindsay and Charlotte: <I>But, Ms. Swamp, we need Ms. Nelson's help with the media</I>.</P>

<P>Someone from the office calls. Sarah has broken her hip and is in the hospital.</P>

<P><B>Frame 3: One girl at the server with Ms. Swamp; another at a desk working on a laptop</B>
<BR>
The school sends a broadcast computer to Sarah so she can connect with her class. Charlotte shows Ms. Swamp how to run the network and teach Sarah using the CompuVision screen.  Lindsay is on the Internet, chatting with someone in Mexico City. Laptop computers are in use throughout the room. A light buzz of voices and keyboard clicks in the background.</P>

<P align=center><IMG SRC="/journal/volume5/2twdraw.gif"></P>

<P><B>Frame 4: A girl in bed</B>
<BR>
Ms. Swamp: <I>Good morning, Sarah. How are you feeling?</I></P>

<P>Sarah: <I>Not too badly, Ms. Swamp. This setup is witchy! I can see and hear you just fine. Jimmy, please get your feet off my desk.</I></P>

<P>Ms. Swamp: <I>Your assignments are on your screen now. Do you have any questions?</I></P>

<P>Sarah:<I> Yes, has Lindsay reached Nancita Ram&oacute;n in Mexico yet?</I></P>

<P><B>Frame 5: Hispanic girl in library with book</B>
<BR>
Lindsay:<I> Wait one, Sarah. Charlotte, can you help me with the split screen commands?</I></P>

<P>[Two girls appear on the CompuVision.]</P>

<P>Ms. Swamp: <I>Hi, Nancita.</I></P>

<P>Nancita: <I>Buenos d&iacute;as. Sorry to hear about your fall, Sarah. I did get the diary translated. It should be coming out of your classroom printer now. It has all the data you need. Meet you on the Web Friday at 2:00. Adi&oacute;s.</I></P>

<P><B>Frame 6: Two girls in classroom using fancy equipment</B>
<BR>
Charlotte:<I> I'll ask Nancita to send us photos of the artifacts and Ram&oacute;n's grave. I will scan them into the video and author the CD. Lindsay, can you generate titles and barcodes for the presentation graphics on your laptop?</I></P>

<P>Lindsay: <I>Sure, and I'll get sound effects from the library. Mission bells, hoof beats, maybe even &#147;Bolero&#148; for the background. We may pull this off yet!</I></P>

<P><B>Frame 7: Two girls, teacher, and Sarah on laptop at table in classroom</B>
<BR>
Lindsay:<I> In 1716, Domingo Ram&oacute;n brought the first European women to East Texas. Sarah tells how the Karankawa Indians and the French drove the missionaries off in 1719. I tell about their escape to San Antonio, and Nancita covers Ram&oacute;n's last days in Mexico. We have the museum's videodisc of his belongings, his diary, and flag.</I></P>

<P>Ms. Swamp:<I> Excellent, dearies.</I></P>

<P><B>Frame 8: The presentation in progress</B>
<BR>
Lindsay and Charlotte are speaking to an attentive audience of their peers. Nancita in seen on the CompuVision, while Sarah is projected onto a pull-down screen. They give their 20-minute multimedia presentation, &#147;Three Hundred Years Ago This Month.&#148; Ms. Swamp watches from the side.</P>

<P><B>Frame 9: Hispanic girl with flag</B>
<BR>
Nancita: <I>So, 300 years ago, Captain Domingo Ram&oacute;n led 12 priests, 25 soldiers, and 7 families from Spain to East Texas. Eventually, the survivors settled in San Antonio. Mission records show that my ancestor moved to Mexico City in 1725, where he died in 1731. He's buried in the church behind me. This is the flag he brought with him from Spain. Do you have any questions?</I></P>

<P><B>Frame 10: Charlotte hugs Lindsay; Sarah watches from the laptop screen</B>
<BR>
Charlotte: <I>We did it, Lindsay. Ms. Swamp, did you like it?</I> [pause] <I>Ms. Swamp? Where is she?</I></P>

<P>Sarah:<I> Look behind you! It's Ms. Nelson. She's back.</I></P>

<P>Charlotte: <I>Ms. Nelson, you missed our project. We did it all by ourselves.</I></P>

<P>Ms. Nelson: <I>Yes, you did. I hope you put it on disc, dearies.</I></P>

<P>Girls: <I>Dearies? You're her. You're Ms. Swamp. You tricked us! You made us do all this work.</I></P>

<P>Ms. Nelson: <I>Yes, and look at the great job you did, dearies.</I></P>


<HR>
<A HREF="/journal/volume5/2carter.htm"><P>Return to <I>Computers in the Classroom of the Future</I> TECHNOS Quarterly article.</P></A>

<P><A HREF="/ait/aitcopy.htm">&copy; AIT</A></P>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
