<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>TECHNOS Quarterly</H1>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>For Education and Technology</H2>
<HR>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Biography</I></H1>
<BR>
<P><B>Joan Mazur</B>, assistant professor of instructional design and technology at the University of Kentucky in Lexington, is involved in technology implementation in schools throughout the state of Kentucky. Her current research and design efforts center on the use of multimedia cases and networks to foster teacher professionalism and educational reform. Her most recent research with veteran teachers using Internet videoconferencing tools indicates enormous potential to promote innovative pedagogy.</P>

