<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>BUSINESS GROWTH
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<body text="#001831" link="#001831" vlink="#001831" background="../images/smallicons/Icon_frmbckgrd2.gif">
<p><br>
<center>
<table cellpadding="12" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="600">
<tr>
<td>
<font face="Helvetica" size="6">BUSINESS GROWTH</font><br>



	Mann Packing Company is the 14th largest employer in Monterey County. Our employment growth pattern is as follows:<pre>

			1989		235 employees
			1990		273 employees
			1991		243 employees
			1992		335 employees
			1993		432 employees
			1994		612 employees
</pre>
	Employee safety and productivity are foremost goals at Mann Packing. In 1992 we started an employee Wellness Program that is designed to develop healthy minds and bodies of the some 600 employees that work for us.
<p>
	Classes to learn to speak, read and write English are available to employees as well as basic math courses. All of these classes are offered free of charge. Should employees choose to further their education even more, Mann Packing offers an Educational Assistance Program to employees with one year of employment or more with the company. 
<p>
	The Educational Assistance Program offers financial aid to employees wishing to take a job-related course at an accredited school, college or university. The percentage of reimbursement offered depends on the grade received. Since the programs inception two years ago, one Mann employee has completed a bachelor of science in business management from Golden Gate University. Another employee was this years valedictorian at Hartnell College and dozens of others have earned credentials and credits through various courses and institutions.
<p>
	At Mann Packing Company we believe that investing in our employees future benefits the company greatly. The more they learn - the more they have to contribute. Job training is on-going, but at Mann Packing we try to take it one step further by investing in the employee. 
<p>
	The Employee Wellness Program also includes health clinics that cover such topics as: low-fat cooking, AIDS awareness, seminars on how to use the companys health insurance, and health screenings which monitor weight, cholesterol and blood pressure. 
Last year the company also started offering flu shots and sponsoring blood drives. The Salinas Police Department also comes in occasionally to speak to the night crews about night safety. 
<p>
	Mann Packing has an active safety program which has enabled us to lower our classification risk considerably over the past eight years. For instance, in 1988 our classification risk was at 239, far above the 100 average for agriculture businesses. Today, our classification averages 78, well below the industry average. The fact that we were able to lower this number significantly, while increasing the number of employees in production, is something we are very proud of.
<p>
	Our insurance carrier and Pan American Underwriters have given us many awards over the past several years for "our dedication to reducing hazards at our worksite."
<p>
<b>INCREASE OF SALES</b><br>

	Mann Packing Companys sales have increased 130 percent since 1988.  We currently market close to 15,000 acres of broccoli, as well as 2,000 acres of leafy vegetables and 2,600 acres of iceberg lettuce. We ship over 30 different commodities available in over 175 different pack specifications. We shipped close to six million cartons in 1993.
<p>
	Because the company is privately held, no further financial statements are available.

<p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
<center>
<a href="../images/footers/footer.map">
