<html>

<head>
<!-- MANN'S BROCCOLI HISTORY, authored by Glenn Van Der Werff for fine.com  -->
<!--  Created may 1, 1996 by Glenn Van Der Werff  -->
<!--  Last Edited 8/12/96 by gavdw  -->
<title>Mann's History</title>
</head>
<body>
<body text="#001831" background="../images/smallicons/Icon_frmbckgrd2.gif">


<a name="top">


<center>
<table bgcolor="#ffffff" cellpadding="12" width="630" border="0">
<tr>
<td>




<table bgcolor="#ffffff" cellpadding="0" width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td colspan="3">

<b><font size="6" color="#6A006A" face="Helvetica">H.W. "Cy" Mann</font></b>
<br><br>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>





<td width="220" valign="top"><b>

<b><font color="#6A006A" size=+5>I</b></font>n the late 1930s, when the United States was beginning to stretch from the Great Depression, a young Stanford graduate came to Californias Salinas Valley seeking employment.
	<p>

H.W. "Cy" Mann started his agricultural career trimming fruit and lettuce for 40 cents an hour. He loaded grain onto boxcars for a local company and through hard work and dedication, eventually became foreman of a produce shed.
	<p>
<img border="1" src="../images/history/HISTORIYPHIL16.jpg"><p>
It was 1939 when a fresh carrot packing operation opened called, quite simply, H.W. Mann. It was soon thereafter that Mr. Mann found his niche in the fresh vegetable industry. It was broccoli.
	<p><font size=+2><i><b><font color="#6A006A">Today, H.W. Mann is Mann Packing Company, Incorporated and the largest shippers of fresh broccoli in the world</font>
	</font></i></b><br>-as well as a shipper of over 35 fresh vegetable commodities. Packed under the famous MANNs Sunny Shores and Sunny Shores labels, these commodities are available in retail and foodservice pack specifications.
	<p>

<img border="1" src="../images/history/HISTORYPHIL19.jpg"><p>
In 1976 Mr. Mann welcomed Bill Ramsey and Don Nucci as partners in the firm. Ramsey joined Mann in 1955 where he directed growing and harvesting operations. Today he serves as co-ceo and president and directs Manns quality systems in field operations. 
	
</font>
 <p>
  <a href="#top">
  <font size="4" color="#6A006A"> Top</font>
  </a>

</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>

<td width="220" valign="top"><b>

<p>In 1967 Don Nucci came on board as office manager. He currently is co-ceo and chief financial officer. He directs all of Manns sales and marketing efforts. Together Mann, Ramsey, and Nucci lead a team of quality personnel which have built the company into one of the most well-respected organizations in the fresh vegetable industry.
	<p>
<img border="1" src="../images/history/HISTORYPHIL.jpg"><p>
<font color="#6A006A"><font size=+5><b>M</b></font></font>r. Mann always said, "Our future always depends on a good reputation for a quality pack supported through merchandising. We survive ever-growing competition because of our adherence to quality. We give our customers full value and treat them fairly. This is why we continue to grow."
	<p>The year 1996 marks the passing of Mr. Mann at the age of 86. While he is missed by  his friends and family every day, he has left a strong foundation for the company to build on and employees at the company are committed to running the business by the standards he set for the company.
	<p>
<img border="1" src="../images/history/HISTORYPHIL17.jpg"><p>
Mann Packing remains a family-owned operation with strong ties to the local community. Generations of families have grown vegetables for the company and many veteran employees have generations of their families at work for the firm.
	<p>
<img border="1" src="../images/history/HISTORIYPHIL18.jpg"><p>
At Mann Packing adherence to quality is the key to success. This adherence is found in every facet of operation where customer service is a part of everyones job description.
<p>
</font>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>

<td valign="top" width="100">
<table width="100" bgcolor="#FEF9D1" border="1" bordercolor="#CF1320" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
<td>
<font color="#6A006A"><b>
<i> "Our future always depends on a good reputation for a quality pack supported through merchandising. We survive ever-growing competition because of our adherence to quality. We give our customers full value and treat them fairly. This is why we continue to grow."<br><b>-H.W. "Cy" Mann</b>
</i></font>
</td>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>



</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
<a href="../images/footers/footer.map">
<IMG SRC="../images/footers/farmbutt.gif" ismap border="0"></a></center>
	
</center>



</body>
