<HEAD>

<TITLE>Broccoli Facts(Production)
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<body text="#001831" link="#001831" vlink="#001831" background="../images/smallicons/Icon_frmbckgrd2.gif">
<p><br>
<center>
<table cellpadding="12" bgcolor="#ffffff" width="600">
<tr>
<td>
<font face="Helvetica" size="6">Broccoli Facts(Production)</font><br>

<b>
Broccoli is the second largest crop grown in Monterey County, California (The Salad Bowl of the World) right behind iceberg lettuce and ahead of strawberries. <p>
<img src="../images/salinas/chart.jpg">

<font size="4"><b>Broccoli Exports</b></font><br>
Broccoli was the top vegetable exported out of Monterey County in 1995 with 139,810,000 pounds leaving the country. Canada, Japan, Hong Kong and Taiwan were the four most popular destinations. 


<p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
