<html>

<head>
<!-- MANN'S SHOPPING/STORAGE TIPS, authored by Glenn Van Der Werff for fine.com  -->
<!--  Created 5/20/96 by gavdw  -->
<!--  Last Edited 7/24/96 by gavdw  -->
<title>Shopping & Storing tips</title>
</head>
<body>
<body background="../images/smallicons/Icon_mombckgrd4.gif">
<br>
<center>

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFEBD7" border="1" cellpadding="12">

<tr>
<td colspan="3" width="600" align="center">
	<font face="Helvetica" color="#6A006A" size=7>
	Shopping and Storing</font>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width="300" valign="top">
<font size="3"><b>

	<b><i><font color="red" size=+7>
B</b></i></font>roccoli stalks should have tight and compact bud clusters with an even dark green or purplish green color.  The stalk should be easy to pierce with a fingernail.  Different varieties of broccoli come in colors ranging from deep sage green to purplish green. 
<p>
Broccoli stems should be a lighter green than the buds, tender and slightly moist.  Avoid broccoli stalks with yellowed or open bud clusters or stems that are hard and dry.  Also avoid broccoli with soft, slippery water-soaked spots of the bud cluster.  Broccoli is usually sold by the one-pound bunch;  check the weigh to get the best value.  The size of the head has no relation to eating quality.
<p>
		Early decay is caused when there is a break in the *"Cold Chain". Ideally, vegetables should be refrigerated within 30 minutes after purchase. </font>
</td>

<td width="304" valign="top">
<font size="3"><b>

Store broccoli in plastic bag in refrigerator crisper -do not rinse. With proper refrigeration  (34 - 40 degrees) you should enjoy as much as 16 days of safe delicious eating.  Please note The vitamin content will remain higher if your fresh broccoli is used as quickly as possible.
	<p>
After opening a bag of vegetables, simply seal the freshness by twisting the bag closed and using a rubber band or twist tie for a secure hold. To ensure our quality, Manns fresh-cut vegetables have the Best If Used By Date conveniently printed on the front of all packages.
<p>
<b><i><font color="red" size=+7>A</b></i></font>ll of Manns fresh-cut vegetables (except Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry) can be frozen.  Before freezing, **blanch the product.  The product should be eaten within 30 days.  Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw should not be frozen unless later used as an ingredient for cooking.  In this case simply blanch and freeze.
</font>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td colspan="2" width="600">
	<font color="#007700"><font size=-1>
	*Cold Chain refers to the process of keeping the product cold in each link of the distribution chain (i.e., from field to shipper to supermarket to your refrigerator)
	<p>
	** The term blanching refers to the process of lightly cooking raw product for varying amounts of time in boiling water with or without salt or vinegar. The product  is then refreshed in cold water and drained or simply to stop the cooking process.

	</font></font>
</td>
</tr>

</table>
<p>
