<html>
<head>
<!-- MANN'S BROCCOLI created 8/15/96 by gavdw   -->
<!--  Last Edited 8/15/96 by Glenn Van Der Werff  -->

<title>Milk and Cheese Group</title>

</head><body background="../images/smallicons/Icon_umbckgrd.gif">
<br>
<center>
<table bgcolor="#ffffff" width="600" cellpadding="12" border="0">
<tr>
<td> 
<center>
 <img src="../images/education/milk.jpg">
</center>
<b><font size="4">Milk and Cheese Group</font><br>
This group provides calcium and protein.  Calcium promotes strong bones and teeth.<p>
<font size="4">Quesadillas</font><br>
Tortillas<br>
Cheese (cheddar or jack)<br>
Onion <br>
Taco sauce<p>
Heat a tortilla in a slightly oiled frying pan.  Put cheese slices on one half of the tortilla; then add an onion slice (fried or raw ) and a little taco sauce (green is food).  Fold and heat the tortilla until the cheese melts.  Quesadillas are good for breakfast or as a snack.<p>
<font size="4">Cottage Cheese Dip</font><br>
Mix together one pound (two cups [454 g]) creamed cottage chese; one-fourth cup (38 g) minced green pepper; 1 tablespoon (5 g) finely snipped chives or parsley.  Dried onions or bacon bits also may be added.<p>
Suggested vegetables for this dip are carrot and celery sticks, cauliflower nibbles, or cherry tomatoes.

</td></tr>  </table><p><a href="../images/footers/footer.map"><IMG SRC="../images/footers/instbutt.gif" ismap border="0"></a></center><p></body></html>
</DOC>
