<title>About Tom</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFEBD7">
<center>
<table bgcolor="#ffffff" width="600" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
<td valign="center" colspan="2">
<img src="../images/ALLABOUTTOM.jpg"><font color="#000080" size="7"><b>All About Tom</font></b></font>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="300">
Tom Livingston, the Director of Foodservice at Mann Packing Company, scored his first major foodservice success at the age of eleven. He found that adding a few ounces of his Dads Jack Daniels to his Mothers Toll House Cookie dough brought him fame if not fortune. At least, when he took the cookies to school, they made him the most popular kid in his fifth grade class.
<P>
After college, Tom, who likes to write, published a novel, took the money and went to live in Europe for six years where he learned first hand about French, Spanish, Portuguese and Italian food and wine by eating and drinking as much of each as he could.
<p>
Later he became head of promotions for Saga Food Service, and still later, vice president of marketing for the health care and Canadian divisions of Saga Corporation. Saga, a $1 billion foodservice contract management and restaurant holding company was acquired by Marriott in 1985. At the time, it was the largest college feeder in the country.
</td>
<td valign="top" width="300">
Tom also served as senior vice president/creative director of a major San Francisco foodservice advertising agency, where he was responsible for creating foodservice ads for the Alaskan Seafood Marketing Institute, the Idaho Potato Commission, the California Strawberry Commission, the Idaho-Oregon Onion Promotion Committee, the California Date Advisory Committee,  the California Iceberg Lettuce Commission, Dole Packaged Foods Company, Farmland Foods, Inc., and the New Zealand Fruit Company.
<p>
He has served as a consultant for such clients as Marriott Corporation, Service America, Inc. and the Refectory Restaurants.
</td>
</tr>

</table>
<p>
<a href="../images/footers/footer.map">
<IMG SRC="../images/footers/foodbutt.gif" ismap border="0"></a>

</center>

</body>
</html>
