<title>Foodservice Facts</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFEBD7">
<center>
<table bgcolor="#ffffff" width="600" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

<font color="green"><h1>Foodservice Web Sites</h1></font>


<a href="http://www.foodservice.ca/fsh/fsh.htm">
Foodservice and Hospitality Magazine</a><br>
Canada's magazine devoted to the foodservice industry - 

Delivering editorial innovation, timeliness and excellence... always!!
Serving Canada's $27.7 billion foodservice industry
Primary readership: 25,000 hospitality owners, managers, chefs and
buyers

<p>

<a href="http://www.foodnet.com">
Foodnet</a><br>
 An online information resouce for food professionals The site is broken into three catagories, Consumer
     Food Editors, Foodservice Editors and FoodPros.

<p>
<a href="http://www.foodservice.org">
Foodservice Connection</a><br>
For professionals in the foodservice industries; features news articles, employment
     opportunities, industry research statistics, TABR, and more. 

<p>
<a href="http://www.foodshow.com">
Foodshow </a><br> Complete foodservice manufacturer product information for operators including merchandising, sampling,
     rebates and recipe opportunities. Food service industry news, education and event calendar. 


<p>
<a href="http://www.restaurant.org/forecast/forecstf.htm">
 1996 Foodservice Industry Forecast Index </a>
 1996 Foodservice Industry Forecast Index 1996 
      
     
<p>
 <a href="http://www.foodservice.org/assoc/tra/"> 
 FoodService: Texas Restaurant Association </a><br>

       FoodService: Texas Restaurant Association [TRA HEADER] ]Southwest Foodservice Expo The most
       up-to-date information about the 1996 Southwest Foodservice Expo for attendees.

<p>


 <a href="http://www.bus.msu.edu/broad/shb/ha/sfm2.htm ">
 SOCIETY FOR FOODSERVICE MANAGEMENT (SFM) </a><br>

      SOCIETY FOR FOODSERVICE MANAGEMENT (SFM) The Society for Foodservice Management (SFM)

<p>
<a href="http://www.vyne.com/bcc/foodbev/GA078.html"> 
 
      GA-078 THE CHANGING COMMERCIAL AND INSTITUTIONAL FOODSERVICE INDUSTRY</a><br>
      
      DOROTHY KROLL PROJECT ANALYST INTRODUCTION STUDY
      

<p>
      <a href="http://www.menu-net.com/sn/jp.foodservice/JP4.htm ">
JP Foodservice, Inc. </a><br>
      JP Foodservice, Inc. Value Added Service JP Foodservice, Inc. serves its customers better, faster and more
      efficiently than anyone else can. 

<p>

<a href="www.culinaryarts.com/specman.htm">
School Info Summary</a><br>
 This course is an up-to-date course on food safety and sanitation - combining food safety and current
        issues on sanitation. This lecture and demonstration course provides the student with a balance of theoretical and
        practical information, helping the student understand the why and how of quality baking.
<p>
<a href="www.Ira.org/expo2.htm">
        1996 Louisiana Foodservice Exposition</a><br>
        Summary: SHOULD ATTEND THE 1996 EXPO: ... Several hundred of the leading suppliers to the industry will
        be gathered under one roof to tell you about their products and services. .. Dieticians SPECIAL EVENTS One of
        the key benefits offered by the Louisiana Foodservice EXPO is the sense of community that people derive from
        attending.

<p>

<a href="http://www.tc.net/foodgroup/">
 Food Group Web Page</a><br>
Your Source For The Hottest Recipes, Promotions and Profit-Builders in Foodservice.

<p>
<a href="http://www.jwu.edu">
Johnson & Wales University</a><br>
Review: This is the Home Page of Johnson & Wales University in Rhode Island, 'the largest foodservice and hospitality educator in the
world.' It offers links to its different campuses, the Department of Culinary Arts, The Department of Hospitality, Business, Trave...


<p>
<a href="www.gbd.com/foodserv.com">
Green Bee Designs, Inc.</a><br> 
 Foodservice design consultants, specializing in the design of commercial kitchens for
     institutions, hotels, restaurants and fast food units. 
