<!-- ************************************************************* -->

<font size="7" color="#004080"> Letters From  Club Members</font>
<img align="right" src="../images/broccotom.gif">
</center>

<!------------------------ Start table one ---------------------------->





<p>
<img border="0" height="25" width="25" src="../images/brocmedtr.gif">

<b><font size="4" color="#6A006A">
 DOES BROCCOLI GROW ON A TREE?<br>
- MERRISA JACKSON, PARKERSBURG, WV, AGE 4</font>

<p>

Not yet Merrisa,  so far broccoli grows close to the ground (like flowers which bloom from seed) in a soil with a good moisture supply.
<p>
<img border="0" height="25" width="25" src="../images/brocmedtr.gif">

<font size="4" color="#6A006A">
Why do people eat broccoli?<br>
- Jon Knash, Valparaiso, IN, age9
</font><p>
For  so many reasons, Jon... 
a few reasons people like it is because it tastes good, 
and because it holds so many important things for healthy bodies.  
It's the vitamin vegetable!!!!! 
<p>
</td>
</tr>
