<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>BROCCOLI RECIPES</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=5>KIDS BROCCOLI RECIPES<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
VEGETABLE SOUP
<P>
6-8 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  15 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  25 minutes<BR>

<P>
1 tsp.  Vegetable oil
<P>
1 cup   Broccoli Wokly&#174; florettes
<P>
1 cup  Carrots, chopped
<P>
1 cup  Celery, sliced
<P>
1/2 cup  Onion, sliced
<P>
1 can (28 oz.) Tomatoes
<P>
1/2 cup  Parsley leaves
<P>
1 clove  Fresh garlic, chopped
<P>
2 cans  Chicken broth
<P>
1/3 cup  Pasta
<P>
2 Tbs.  Parmesan cheese, grated<BR>

<P>
Over medium heat, heat oil in a saucepan.  Add onion and garlic,
cook until onion is soft (about 2-3 minutes).<BR>

<P>
Add pasta, parsley, tomatoes and chicken broth.  Bring to a boil,
reduce heat and simmer for an additional 10 minutes.<BR>

<P>
Add carrots and celery, cook for 5 minutes and add broccoli, cook
for an additional 10 minutes.  Add salt and pepper to taste.<BR>

<P>
BROCCOLI WOKLY&#174; PIZZA
<P>
2-4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  15 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  10 minutes<BR>

<P>
1 lg.  Boboli bread
<P>
2 cups   Broccoli Wokly&#174; florettes, chopped and blanched
<P>
8 oz.  Commercial or home made pizza sauce
<P>
1 Tbs.  Olive oil
<P>
1 Tbs.  Fresh Garlic, chopped
<P>
1 cup  Mozzarella cheese, shredded (more or less if desired)<BR>

<P>
Saut&eacute; olive oil and fresh garlic until garlic is just turning
golden.  Spread evenly over Boboli bread.  Spread pizza sauce
to taste.  Layer Mozzarella cheese and broccoli over pizza.  Bake
according to the directions on Boboli bread package.<BR>

<P>
Suggestions:;  Add mushrooms, pepperoni, onions, olives or whatever
your favorite topping may be.
<P>
 BROCCOLI SPAGHETTI PARMESAN
<P>
4-6 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  5 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  10 minutes<BR>

<P>
2-1 lb. pkgs. Broccoli Wokly&#174; florettes, coarsely chopped
<P>
1-1 lb. pkg. Spaghetti (or any type of pasta you prefer)
<P>
1/2 tsp. Garlic salt
<P>
2 Tbs.  Olive oil
<P>
1/2 cup  Butter or margarine
<P>
2-3 cloves Garlic, crushed
<P>
2 Tbs. Parmesan cheese (more or less if desired)<BR>

<P>
Bring water and garlic salt to boil in a pot.  Cook spaghetti
according to the directions on the spaghetti package.  Five minutes
before spaghetti is done cooking, add Broccoli Wokly&#174;.  Drain.
<BR>

<P>
Plaice spaghetti and broccoli in a large bowl and toss with olive
oil, butter and garlic.  Salt and pepper to taste.  May be served
hot or cold.<BR>

<P>
Note Garlic may always be increased depending on personal preference.
<BR>

<P>
EASY BROCCOLI WOKLY&#174; &amp; BEEF
<P>
3-4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  10 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:   15 minutes<BR>

<P>
1-1 oz. pkg. Stir Fry Seasoning Mix
<P>
1 lb.  Broccoli Wokly&#174; florettes
<P>
2 Tbs.  Vegetable oil, divided
<P>
1/2 lb.  Boneless tender beef, cut in thin strips
<P>
1 lg.  onion, chopped<BR>

<P>
Dissolve mix in 2/3 cup water and set aside.  Heat 1 Tbs. oil
in hot wok or large skillet over high heat; add beef.  Stir fry
for approximately 1 minute, remove.  <BR>

<P>
Heat remaining 2 Tbs. oil in same pan.  Add broccoli and onion;
stir-fry for 4 minutes, sprinkling with 1 Tbs. water after 2 minutes.
 Add beef, and seasoning mixture.  Stir until sauce boils and
thickens and beef and vegetables are coated with sauce.<BR>

<P>
Serve over rice.
<P>
MANN&iacute;S CALIFORNIA ROASTED VEGETABLES
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  10 minutes
<P>
Cook Time: 40-45 minutes<BR>

<P>
3 1/2 Tbs. Butter or olive oil (melted)
<P>
1 1/2 Tbs. Fresh parsley, chopped or 1 1/2 tsp. dried parsley
flakes
<P>
1 clove  Garlic, crushed
<P>
1/4 tsp. Salt (more or less if desired)
<P>
1-1lb. pkg. Mann&iacute;s Vegetable Medley
<P>
To taste Freshly ground pepper<BR>

<P>
Preheat oven to 375.  IN a 9 X 13 inch baking dish, combine melted
butter, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper, mixing to blend well.
  Stir in vegetable medley, tossing well to coat with butter mixture.
<BR>

<P>
Bake uncovered, stirring once, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
<P>
EASY ASIAN STIR FRY
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  10 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  15 minutes<BR>

<P>
3 Tbs.  Vegetable oil
<P>
1-1lb. pkg. Broccoli Wokly&#174; Stir Fry
<P>
3 Tbs.  Stir fry sauce (regular or spicy Szechwan style)<BR>

<P>
In a large wok or skillet, heat oil until hot but not smoking.
 Add vegetables and cook over medium-high heat, stirring and tossing,
until broccoli turns bright green, 1 to 2 minutes.<BR>

<P>
Add sauce and stir-fry until vegetables are glazed and crisp-tender,
30 seconds to 1 minute longer.  Serve alone or over rice.<BR>

<P>
ASIAN BROCCO BURRITO
<P>
8 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:   20 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  10 minutes<BR>

<P>
4 tsp.  Vegetable oil
<P>
1-1lb. pkg. Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;
<P>
1/2 cup  Onion, chopped
<P>
4 cloves Garlic, crushed
<P>
1 lb.  Ground turkey
<P>
8   Burrito size flour tortillas (9-10 inches in diameter)
<P>
1/3 cup  Szechwan Spicy Stir Fry Sauce
<P>
1/2 tsp. Chinese 5-Spice powder
<P>
2 cups (8 oz.) Monterey Jack, shredded
<P>
  Bottled Chinese Plum Sauce<BR>

<P>
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.  In a wok or large skillet, heat
1 Tbs. of the oil until hot but not smoking.  Add Mann&iacute;s
Broccoli Cole Slaw and cook, stirring and tossing, until crisp-tender,
about 2 minutes.  Using tongs or a large slotted spoon, transfer
broccoli cole slaw to a large bowl.<BR>

<P>
In the same wok or skillet, add the remaining teaspoon of oil,
if needed.  Cook onion and garlic over medium heat until onion
is softened but not browned, 3 to 5 minutes.  Increase heat to
medium-high, add ground turkey and cook, stirring to break up
the chunks of meat, until the turkey is lightly browned on the
outside and no trace of pink remains, 8 to 10 minutes.<BR>

<P>
Meanwhile, wrap tortillas in foil and heat in the oven for 10
minutes to soften.<BR>

<P>
Stir the turkey mixture in the cooked broccoli cole slaw, adding
the Szechwan Spicy Stir-Fry Sauce and Chinese 5-Spice powder to
coat.  Mix the cheese.<BR>

<P>
For each burrito, place about 3/4 cup of filling just below the
center of a tortilla.  Fold in one side and then fold up from
the bottom, enclosing the filling.  Fold in the other side of
tortilla and serve warm, with Chinese Plum Sauce for dipping.
<P>
GARDEN TUNA SALAD WRAP
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  15  minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  10 minutes<BR>

<P>
1 1/2 cups Broccoli Wokly&#174; florettes
<P>
4   Burrito size flour tortillas (9-10 inches in diameter)
<P>
1-6 oz. can Tuna, drained and flaked
<P>
2/3 cup  Tartar sauce, purchased or homemade
<P>
2 1/2 Tbs. Green onions, chopped
<P>
2 Tbs.  Celery, finely chopped
<P>
1 1/2 tsp. Fresh lemon juice<BR>

<P>
Preheat oven to 35o degrees.  In a medium saucepan filled with
boiling salted water, blanch broccoli by cooking just until it
turns bright green.  Drain in a colander and rinse with cold water
to set the color; drain again.<BR>

<P>
Wrap tortillas in foil and heat in the oven 10 minutes to soften.
<BR>

<P>
In a medium bowl, mix together the blanched broccoli, tuna, tarter
sauce, green onions, celery and lemon juice.  For each broccoli
wrap, place about 1/2 cup of tuna salad just below the center
of a tortilla.  Fold in one side and then fold up from the bottom,
enclosing the filling.  Fold in the other side of the tortilla.
 Serve at once, or wrap tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerate
up to 4 hours.<BR>

<P>
GRAB &amp; GO VEGGIE PITA
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:   10 minutes<BR>
<BR>

<P>
2 cups   Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;
<P>
2/3 cup  Hummus (Middle Eastern chick-pea dip)
<P>
4 tsp.  Pickled jalape&ntilde;o peppers, finely chopped
<P>
2   Plain or whole wheat pita breads (about 6 inches in diameter
<P>
4-8  Fresh tomato, sliced<BR>

<P>
In a medium bowl, mix together Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;,
hummus and jalape&ntilde;o peppers.<BR>

<P>
Using kitchen scissors or a sharp knife, cut pita breads in half.
 Fill each pita half with 1 or 2 tomato slices and 1/2 cup of
the broccoli slaw-hummus mixture.<BR>

<P>
BROCCO TACO&#153; SALAD
<P>
6-8 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:    15 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  10 minutes<BR>

<P>
1-1lb. bag Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;
<P>
1-8 oz. can Red kidney beans, drained
<P>
1 cup  Cheddar cheese, shredded
<P>
1 lg.  Tomato, sliced
<P>
1-2 1/4 oz. can Black olives, drained and sliced
<P>
1/2 cup  Thousand island dressing (optional)
<P>
1/4 cup  Red onion, finely chopped
<P>
1/4 cup  Salsa
<P>
1 lb.  Ground beef or turkey
<P>
1-10.5 oz. bag Corn chips, such as Fritos&#174; or tortilla chips
<P>
  Salt and pepper to taste<BR>

<P>
In a large bowl, combine Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;,
kidney beans, Cheddar cheese, tomato, olives and onion, tossing
to mix well.  Add salad dressing and salsa tossing again to coat.
(Salad can be made up to this point 24 hours in advance, cover
and refrigerate.)<BR>

<P>
If using ground beef/turkey option, in a large skillet over medium-high
heat, cook ground beef, stirring to break up the chunks of meat,
until nicely browned on the outside and no trace of pink remains,
8-10 minutes.  Let cool.  Add to salad mixture before adding salad
dressing and toss well to mix.<BR>

<P>
BROCCO BURGER&#153;
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:   15 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:   10 minutes<BR>

<P>
1 cup  Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;
<P>
1 cup  Cooked brown rice
<P>
1/3 cup  Kidney beans, drained
<P>
1/3 cup  Mushrooms, coarsely chopped
<P>
1/4 cup  Parmesan cheese, freshly grated
<P>
2   Egg whites
<P>
2 tsp.  Taco seasoning<BR>

<P>
Preheat oven to 500 degrees.  In a blender or food processor,
combine the broccoli cole slaw, cooked brown rice, kidney beans,
mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, egg whites and taco seasoning.  Process,
scraping down the sides of the work bowl once or twice with a
rubber spatula, until the ingredients are finely chopped and well
blended.<BR>

<P>
For mixture into 4 equal patties and place on a lightly oiled
baking sheet.  Bake until patties are firm and brown at the edges,
about 10 minutes.  To serve, use a spatula to invert the patty
so browned-side faces up.  (Alternatively, patties can be pan
-fried in a skillet for 3-4 minutes).<BR>

<P>
STEAMED VEGETABLES
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:   10 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:    10 minutes<BR>

<P>
1-14 1/2 oz. can Swanson&#174; ready to serve clear vegetable
broth
<P>
1-1 lb. pkg.  Mann&iacute;s Vegetable Medley<BR>

<P>
In a saucepan, bring broth and vegetables to a boil over medium-high
heat. Cook and cover  over low heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables
are tender.<BR>

<P>
CAULIETTES&#153; with  CHEESE SAUCE DIJONNAISE
<P>
8 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:    10 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:    5 minutes<BR>

<P>
1-10 1/4 oz. can Campbell&iacute;s&#174; condensed Cheddar cheese
soup
<P>
1/3 cup   Milk
<P>
1 Tbs.   Dijon-style mustard
<P>
2-12 oz. pkgs.  Mann&iacute;s Cauliettes&#153;, cooked and drained
<BR>

<P>
In a saucepan, mix soup, milk and mustard, Heat through over low
heat  stirring frequently.  Serve over cauliflower.<BR>

<P>
VEGETABLE ROTINI
<P>
6 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:   15 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  20 minutes<BR>

<P>
2 1/2 cups  Corkscrew macaroni, dry
<P>
4 cups   Mann&iacute;s Broccoli &amp; Carrots
<P>
1-3 oz. pkg.  Cream Cheese, softened
<P>
1-10 1/4 oz. can Campbell&iacute;s&#174; condensed broccoli cheese
soup
<P>
3/4 cup   Milk
<P>
2 Tbs.   Dijon-style mustard (optional)
<P>
1/2 cup   Parmesan cheese, grated
<P>
1/8 tsp.  Pepper<BR>

<P>
In a saucepan, prepare macaroni according to directions on the
package.  Add broccoli and carrots for the last 5 minutes of cooking.
 Drain in a colander.<BR>

<P>
In the same pan, stir cream cheese until smooth.  (to soften,
remove cream cheese from wrapper, place on microwave-safe plate
and microwave on high for 10 seconds)  Stir in soup, milk, mustard,
Parmesan cheese and pepper.  Heat through over low heat.  Add
macaroni and vegetables.  Heat thoroughly.  Serve.<BR>

<P>
SKILLET CHICKEN &amp; BROCCOLI WOKLY&#174;
<P>
4 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  10 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  25 minutes<BR>

<P>
1 Tbs. Margarine or butter
<P>
4  Boneless chicken breast halves
<P>
1-10 1/4 can Campbell&iacute;s&#174; condensed broccoli cheese
soup
<P>
1/3 cup  Water or milk
<P>
1/8 tsp. Pepper
<P>
2 cups  Mann&iacute;s Broccoli Wokly&#174;<BR>

<P>
In a skillet, heat margarine over medium-high heat.  Cook chicken
10 minutes or until browned.  Set chicken aside.<BR>

<P>
Add soup, water, pepper and broccoli.  Heat to a boil.  Return
chicken to pan.  Cover and cook over low heart 10 minutes or until
the chicken is no longer pink.<BR>

<P>
EASY CHICKEN &amp; BISCUITS
<P>
5 Servings
<P>
Preparation Time:  15 minutes
<P>
Cook Time:  10 minutes<BR>

<P>
1-10 1/4 oz. can Campbell&iacute;s&#174; condensed cream of celery
soup
<P>
1-10 1/4 oz. can Campbell&iacute;s&#174; condensed cream of potato
soup
<P>
1 cup    Milk
<P>
1/4 tsp.  Dry thyme leaves, crushed
<P>
1/4 tsp.  Pepper
<P>
1-1 lb. pkg.  Mann&iacute;s Broccoli &amp; Carrots, cooked and
drained
<P>
2 cups   Chicken, cooked
<P>
1-7 1/2 or 10 oz. pkg. Refrigerated biscuits<BR>

<P>
In a 3 quart shallow baking dish, mix the soups, milk, thyme,
pepper, broccoli, carrots and chicken.<BR>

<P>
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until hot.  Stir.  Arrange
biscuits over chicken and bake for an additional 14 minutes or
until the biscuits are golden brown.
</BODY>

