<!--

Mealtime Lunch Dinner 
Region ( Japan ) 
Kids 
Product Mann's Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry 
Prep time 3 or 4 minutes 

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->
 


 <table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
EASY ASIAN STIR FRY</b></font> 
<p>



<img align="right" src="../../images/foodshots/STIRFRY.jpg">
4 Servings<br>
Preparation Time:  10 minutes<br>
Cook Time:  15 minutes<br>
<p>
3 Tbs.		Vegetable oil<br>
1-1lb. pkg.	Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry<br>
3 Tbs.		Stir fry sauce (regular or spicy Szechwan style)
<p>
In a large wok or skillet, heat oil until hot but not smoking.  Add vegetables and cook over medium-high heat, stirring and tossing, until broccoli turns bright green, 1 to 2 minutes.
<p>
Add sauce and stir-fry until vegetables are glazed and crisp-tender, 30 seconds to 1 minute longer.  Serve alone or over rice.
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
<!--------------------------Add Above Here------------------------->
<a href="../mkrecipestoc.htm">
Back to Mom's Favorite Recipes</a>
<p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</center>
