<html>
<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli
Mealtime Lunch Dinner
Entertaining Pot luck dinners Mother's Day 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->
 


 <table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS MOTHER OF ALL HASHES</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">
We might also name this dish the Mother of all Comfort Foods because it  is so tasty and filling. It will also take the prize for creativity at the next potluck dinner you attend.  And, depending on whether youre a man or a woman, youll be a hero or heroine when you serve it to your family or friends. Using instant mashed potatoes also makes it a snap to put together. 
</font><p>

<img src="../../images/foodshots/hash.jpeg" align=right>

1 large red-skinned potato (about 6 ounces)<br> 
3 cups <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
1 1/2 cups prepared, well seasoned creamy mashed potatoes<br>
4 ounces turkey ham, cut into 1/2-inch dice (about 1 cup)<br>
3/4 cup (3 ounces) shredded sharp Cheddar cheese
<p>
1.Preheat oven to 350.  Grease a 9-inch square baking pan and set aside.  Scrub the potato clean and cut into a 1/2-inch dice.  In a medium saucepan, cover potato cubes with cold salted water and bring to a boil over high heat.  Cook until the potatoes are barely tender when pierced with the tip of a knife, 3 to 5 minutes.  Drain in a colander. 
<p>
2.In a large bowl, combine the potato cubes with <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>, the mashed potatoes and turkey ham, stirring to mix well. Turn mixture into the prepared pan and top with cheese. Cover with foil and bake until heated through, about 25 minutes.  Remove foil and bake until the top is lightly browned, about 5 minutes longer. 
<p>
Serves 8 

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per 4 0z. Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	90	Vitamin A:	121 IU
Protein:	6.8 G	Vitamin C:	26 mg
Carbohydrates:	10 G	Thiamin:	0.05 mg
Dietary Fiber:	1.3 G	Riboflavin: 	0.1 mg
Fat-total:	3 G	Niacin:		1.1 mg
Saturated fat	1.4 G	Calcium:	107 mg
Cholesterol:	17 mg	Iron:		0.8 mg
Sodium:		288 mg	Cal. from Fat:	28 %
</pre>


  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
