<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Lunch Supper 
Entertaining Cookouts Kids Birthday Parties Vegetarian Feasts 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->
 


<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS CRUNCHY BROCCO-BURGER</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">
This may just be the best veggie burger youve ever tasted!  Weve given it a southwestern flair with a bit of taco seasoning; but feel free to vary the spices according to taste.  Serve patties plain topped with a bit of salsa, or serve on a whole wheat hamburger bun with thinly sliced onion, relish, lettuce, tomato and all the other traditional fixins. 
</font><p>

<img src="../../images/foodshots/brocco_burger.jpeg" align=right>

1 cup <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
1 cup freshly cooked brown rice<br>
1/3 cup drained canned kidney beans<br>
1/3 cup coarsely chopped mushrooms<br>
1/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese<br>
2 eggwhites<br>
2 teaspoons taco seasoning
<p>
1.Preheat oven to 500.  In a blender or food processor, combine the <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>, cooked brown rice, kidney beans, mushrooms, 	Parmesan cheese, egg whites and taco seasoning.  Process, scraping 	down the sides of the work bowl once or twice with a rubber spatula, until the ingredients are finely chopped and well blended. 
<p>
2.Form mixture into 4 equal patties and place on a lightly oiled baking sheet. Bake until patties are firm and brown at the edges, about 10 minutes.  To serve, use a spatula to invert the patty so browned-side faces up.  (Alternatively, patties can be pan-fried in a skillet for 3-4 minutes per side.) 
<p>
Serves 4 
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per  4 oz. Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	126	Vitamin A:	110 IU
Protein:	8.3 G	Vitamin C:	19 mg
Carbohydrates:	17 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.4 G	Riboflavin: 	0.2 mg
Fat-total:	2.9 G	Niacin:		1.4 mg
Saturated fat	1.6 G	Calcium:	130 mg
Cholesterol:	6.3 mg	Iron:		0.8 mg
Sodium:		444 mg	Cal. from Fat:	21 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

