<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 8/6/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Lunch Supper 
Entertaining Cookouts Kids Parties Picnics Cinco de Mayo 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
Prep time 10 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS Brocco-Taco SALAD</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">

This cool and crunch entree salad is a taste treat with the ground beef or turkey or without them. So it offers really versatility if you want something new and exciting for your veggie friends. Or, for more traditional tastes, it beats the heck out of a taco salad with lettuce because broccoli is so much more nutritious. Great to stick in the fridge for weekend lunches or suppers--or weekday dinners if youre in a hurry.
</font><p>
<img align="right" src="../../images/foodshots/TACOSALAD.jpg">
1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>
	1 (8 ounce) can red kidney beans, drained<br>
	1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese (4 ounces)<br>
	1 large tomato, diced<br>
	1 (2 1/4 ounce) can sliced black olives, drained<br>
	1/4 cup finely chopped red onion<br>
	1/2 cup Thousand Island salad dressing<br>
	1/4 cup salsa<br>
	1 pound of ground beef or ground turkey (optional)<br>
	1 (10.5 ounce) bag corn chips, such as Fritos or tortilla chips<br>

Salt and pepper to taste



<p>

1. In a large bowl, combine Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw, kidney beans, Cheddar cheese, tomato, olives and onion, tossing to mix well. Add salad dressing and salsa, tossing again to coat. (Salad can be made up to this point 24 hours in advance, cover, and refrigerate.)
 <p>
2. (If using ground beef/turkey option) In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, stirring to break up the chunks of meat, until nicely browned on the outside and no trace of pink remains, 8-10 minutes. Let cool. Add to salad mixture before adding salad dressing and toss well to  mix.

 <p>
3. Drain vermicelli in a colander and pour into a large heated serving bowl.  Add Broccoli-Vera sauce mixture and peas, tossing gently to coat.  Taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper as necessary.  Top each serving with 1 Tablespoon of Parmesan cheese. 

<p>
6-8 Servings


  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
