<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Snack/Appetizer/Lunch/Dinner 
Region (Japan) 
Entertaining Hors d'oeurves, Asian theme dinners 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
Prep time 10 minutes 

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS CRISPY ASIAN BROCCOLI PATTIES</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">
Vegetable patties are a welcome side dish at almost any meal. Prepare them in a traditional patty size or as a smaller bite-size appetizer to serve with drinks.  For convenience, patties can be cooked in advance, refrigerated, and re-heated in a hot oven. 
</font><p>

<img src="../../images/foodshots/asian_patties.jpeg" align=right>

1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
3 eggs, lightly beaten<br>
5 Tablespoons flour<br>
2 1/2 Tablespoons bottled teriyaki glaze<br>
2 1/2 Tablespoons vegetable oil, plus oil for cooking
<p>
1.In a large bowl, mix together the <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>, eggs, flour, teriyaki glaze and the 2 1/2 Tablespoons of vegetable oil. 
<p>
2.On a griddle or in large skillet, warm 1 Tablespoon of oil over medium heat.  Using a 1/4-cup measure, drop batter onto the hot griddle and flatten with the back of a spatula. Cook, turning once, until golden brown on both sides, 2 to 3 minutes total. Drain on paper towels.  Repeat with remaining batter, adding more oil to the grill if necessary. Serve warm. 
<p>
Makes about 1 dozen patties
Serves 4 to 6 
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per 4 oz. Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	164	Vitamin A:	314 IU
Protein:	5 G	Vitamin C:	55 mg
Carbohydrates:	10 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2 G	Riboflavin: 	0.2 mg
Fat-total:	12 G	Niacin:		0.7 mg
Saturated fat	1.9 G	Calcium:	44 mg
Cholesterol:	85 mg	Iron:		1 mg
Sodium:		163 mg	Cal. from Fat:	65 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
