<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Breakfast Lunch Dinner 
Region California  
Entertaining Brunches 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
Prep time 13 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS California Broccoli Home Fries</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">
Potatoes in the morning always make breakfast seem special.  Wake up your taste buds by serving this colorful melange with sausages or bacon and eggs; or serve it alone, with buttered whole wheat toast or warm flour tortillas for impromptu breakfast burritos.  For convenience, potatoes can be cooked the night before, wrapped in a tea towel and refrigerated. 
</font><p>





<img src="../../images/foodshots/ca.broccolihomefries.jpg" align=right>

	2 medium red-skinned potatoes (about 8 ounces total)<br>
	1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
	1 large onion, chopped <br>
	1 large red or green bell pepper, cut into 1/2-inch squares<br>
	Salt and freshly ground pepper<br>
	Vegetable oil for cooking
<p>
1. Scrub the potatoes clean and cut into a 1/2-inch dice.  In a medium saucepan, cover potato cubes with cold salted water and bring to a boil over high heat.  Cook until the potatoes are tender when pierced with the tip of a sharp knife, 5 to 7 minutes.  Drain in a colander. 
 <p>
2. In a large bowl, toss together the potatoes, broccoli cole slaw, onion and bell pepper.  On an oiled griddle or in a large skillet, working in batches if necessary, spread a single layer of the potato and broccoli mixture on the hot griddle, pressing down gently with the back of a spatula.  Season with salt and pepper to taste.  Cook, turning once, until golden on both sides, 2 to 3 minutes total.  Serve warm. 

<p>
4-6 Servings
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per 3 oz. Serving </b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:		90	Vitamin A:	172 IU
Protein:		2 G	Vitamin C:	49 mg
Carbohydrates:	       11.5 G	Thiamin:	0.08 mg
Dietary Fiber:		2.3 G	Riboflavin: 	0.05 mg
Fat-total:		4.5 G	Niacin:	        0.8 mg
Saturated fat		0.6 G	Calcium:	25 mg
Cholesterol:		0 mg	Iron:	        0.7 mg
Sodium:			11 mg	Cal. from Fat:	43 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
