<!-- 
Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime-Snack/Lunch/Dinner 
Region (China/Mexico) 
Entertaining--Cookouts/Kids Birthday Parties 
Product-- Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
-->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  
<p>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040"cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS ASIAN BROCCO BURRITO</b></font>
<p>
<font color="#6A006A">This cross-cultural favorite is a hit with both adults and kids. Gourmet sophisticates call it "fusion cuisine." Serve 1 burrito for a snack, or 2 as a main course--along with plenty of napkins!
</font><p>

<img src="../../images/foodshots/asian_burrito.jpeg" align=right>

4 teaspoons vegetable oil <br>
1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
1/2 cup chopped onion<br>
4 garlic cloves, crushed through a press<br>
1 lb. ground turkey<br>
8 burrito-size flour tortillas (9- to 10-inches in diameter)<br>
1/3 cup bottled Szechwan Spicy Stir-Fry Sauce<br>
1/2 teaspoon Chinese 5-Spice powder<br>
2 cups (8 ounces) shredded Monterey Jack cheese<br>
Bottled Chinese Plum Sauce
<p>
1.  Preheat oven to 350.  In a wok or large skillet, heat 1 Tablespoon of the oil until hot but not smoking.  Add <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b> and cook, stirring and tossing, until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.  Using tongs or a large slotted spoon, transfer broccoli cole slaw to a large bowl. 
<p>
2.  In the same wok or skillet, add the remaining teaspoon of oil if needed. Cook onion and garlic over medium heat until onion is softened but 	not browned, 3 to 5 minutes. Increase heat to medium-high, add 	ground turkey and cook, stirring to break up the chunks of meat, until the turkey is lightly browned on the outside and no trace of pink remains, 8 to 10 minutes. 
<p>
3.  Meanwhile, wrap tortillas in foil and heat in the oven for 10 minutes to soften. 
<p>
4.  Stir the turkey mixture into the cooked broccoli cole slaw, adding the 	Szechwan Spicy Stir-Fry Sauce and Chinese 5-Spice powder to coat. Mix in the cheese. 
<p>
5.  For each burrito, place about 3/4 cup of filling just below the center of a tortilla.  Fold in one side and then fold up from the bottom, enclosing the filling.  Fold in the other side of tortilla and serve warm, with Chinese Plum Sauce for dipping. 
<p>
Makes 8 burritos
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving </b></u>  </font>  
<pre>
Calories:	404	Vitamin A:	310 IU
Protein:	28 G	Vitamin C:	48 mg
Carbohydrates:	26 G	Thiamin:	0.3 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.1 G	Riboflavin: 	0.4 mg
Fat-total:	21 G	Niacin:		4.4 mg
Saturated fat	8 G	Calcium:	304 mg
Cholesterol:	83 mg	Iron:		3.1 mg
Sodium:		734 mg	Cal. from Fat:	47 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>


</td>
</tr>
</table>
