<!--

Mealtime Lunch Dinner
Region Milan Italy
Entertaining Birthday Parties Columbus Day
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw
Prep time 10 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS Pasta Broccoli-Vera</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">

Classic Pasta Primavera is a springtime specialty of many restaurants.  This delicious simplified version can be enjoyed year round and prepared in less than 30 minutes at home. All you need to complete the meal is a crisp green salad, crusty Italian bread and chilled white wine. 
</font><p>
<img src="../../images/foodshots/pastabroccolivera.jpg" align=right>
4 cups <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
	1 cup prepared Alfredo or Parmesan Cream Sauce<br>
	8 ounces vermicelli or other thin spaghetti<br>
	1/2 cup frozen peas, thawed<br>
	Salt and freshly ground pepper<br>
	1/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese


<p>
1. In a medium saucepan, combine Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw with the Alfredo sauce. Cook partially covered over low heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through. 
 <p>
2. Meanwhile, in a large pot of boiling salted water, cook vermicelli according to package directions. 
 <p>
3. Drain vermicelli in a colander and pour into a large heated serving bowl.  Add Broccoli-Vera sauce mixture and peas, tossing gently to coat.  Taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper as necessary.  Top each serving with 1 Tablespoon of Parmesan cheese. 

<p>
4 Servings

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	475	Vitamin A:	325 IU
Protein:	21 G	Vitamin C:	69 mg
Carbohydrates:	57 G	Thiamin:	0.7 mg
Dietary Fiber:	3 G	Riboflavin: 	0.4 mg
Fat-total:	19.2 G	Niacin:		5 mg
Saturated fat	1.5 G	Calcium:	144 mg
Cholesterol:	65 mg	Iron:		3 mg
Sodium:		845 mg	Cal. from Fat:	36 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
