<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->




 <table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  


<tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS GRAB & GO VEGGIE PITA</b></font> 
<p><font color="#6A006A">
This satisfying sandwich gets an unexpected jolt of flavor from jalapeno chile peppers. For those who prefer a milder taste, substitute sliced ripe black olives. Look for prepared hummus in Middle Eastern markets, delicatessens or in the refrigerated deli section of many supermarkets. 
</font><p>

<img src="../../images/foodshots/veggie_pita.jpeg" align=right>

2 cups <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>
2/3 cup hummus (Middle Eastern chick-pea dip), purchased or homemade<br>
4 teaspoons finely chopped pickled jalapeno peppers<br>
2 plain or whole wheat pita breads (about 6-inches in diameter) <br>
4 to 8 fresh tomato slices
<p>
1.In a medium bowl, mix together the <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>, hummus, and jalapeno peppers.
<p>
2.Using kitchen scissors or a sharp knife, cut pita breads in half.  Fill each pita half with 1 or 2 tomato slices and 1/2 cup of the broccoli slaw-hummus mixture. 
<p>
Makes 4 sandwiches
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	189	Vitamin A:	175 IU
Protein:	6.6 G	Vitamin C:	46 mg
Carbohydrates:	31 G	Thiamin:	0.3 mg
Dietary Fiber:	1.8 G	Riboflavin: 	0.2 mg
Fat-total:	4.8 G	Niacin:		2 mg
Saturated fat	0.7 G	Calcium:	72 mg
Cholesterol:	0 mg	Iron:		2 mg
Sodium:		347 mg	Cal. from Fat:	22 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
