<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Mealtime Lunch Dinner 
Region Kyoto Japan
Kids
Product Mann's Vegetable Medley

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!-------------------------------Add Below Here--------------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS Roasted Vegetables Kyoto</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">



Serve this mahogany-glazed vegetable medley alongside anything from chicken to meatloaf, and the vegetables will probably be the first thing to go!  It also makes a great vegetarian entree served over hot steamed rise. 
</font><p>



3 Tablespoons bottled teriyaki glaze<br>
	4 teaspoons vegetable oil <br>
	1 teaspoon grated fresh ginger or 1/4 teaspoon ground ginger <br>
	1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Vegetable Medley</b>
<p>
1. Preheat oven to 375.  In a 9 X 13-inch baking dish, combine teriyaki glaze, oil and ginger, mixing to blend well.  Stir in vegetable medley, tossing well to coat with teriyaki mixture. 
 <p>
2. Bake uncovered, stirring once, until vegetables are crisp-tender, 40 to 45 minutes.


<p>
4 Servings
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per 3 oz. Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	90	Vitamin A:	1121 IU
Protein:	3 G	Vitamin C:	69 mg
Carbohydrates:	10 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	3.1 G	Riboflavin: 	0.1 mg
Fat-total:	5.4 G	Niacin:		1 mg
Saturated fat	0.7 G	Calcium:	43 mg
Cholesterol:	0 mg	Iron:		1 mg
Sodium:		421 mg	Cal. from Fat:	49 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
