<font color="green"><b>
MANNS Roasted Vegetables Provencal</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">





The subtle fragrance of lemon, garlic and thyme brings the flavors of southern French cooking to this colorful vegetable combination. 
</font><p>



3 1/2 Tablespoons melted butter or olive oil <br>
	1 teaspoon fresh lemon juice<br>
	1 garlic clove, crushed through a press<br>
	2 teaspoons chopped fresh thyme or 1/2 teaspoon dried thyme leaves<br>
	1/4 teaspoon salt, or more to taste<br>
	1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Vegetable Medley</b>
	


<p>
1. Preheat oven to 375.  In a 9 X 13-inch baking dish, combine melted butter, lemon juice, garlic, thyme and salt, mixing to blend well.  Stir in vegetable medley, tossing well to coat with butter mixture. 
 <p>
2. Bake uncovered, stirring once, until vegetables are crisp-tender, 40 to 45 minutes. 

<p>
4 Servings

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per 3 oz. Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	123	Vitamin A:	1211 IU
Protein:	2.5 G	Vitamin C:	69 mg
Carbohydrates:	8 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	3 G	Riboflavin: 	0.1 mg
