<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS California Roasted Vegetables</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">

Roasting is quick, easy and brings out the natural sweetness in our fresh-cut garden vegetables.  Serve this at your next family dinner and accept the compliments gracefully.  

</font><p>




	3 1/2 Tablespoons melted butter or olive oil <br>
	1 1/2 Tablespoons chopped fresh parsley or 1 1/2 teaspoons dried parsley flakes <br>
	1 garlic clove, crushed through a press <br>
	1/4 teaspoon salt, or more to taste
	Dash of freshly ground pepper <br>
	1 (1 pound) bag <b>Manns Vegetable Medley</b>

<p>
1. Preheat oven to 375.  In a 9 X 13-inch baking dish, combine melted butter, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper, mixing to blend well.  Stir in vegetable medley, tossing well to coat with butter mixture. 
 <p>
2. Bake uncovered, stirring once, until vegetables are crisp-tender, 40 to 45 minutes. 

<p>
4 Servings

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per 3 oz. Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>

Calories:	123	Vitamin A:	1213 IU
Protein:	2.5 G	Vitamin C:	69 mg
Carbohydrates:	8 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	3 G	Riboflavin: 	0.1 mg
Fat-total:	9.9 G	Niacin:		0.9 mg
Saturated fat	6 G	Calcium:	47 mg
Cholesterol:	26 mg	Iron:		0.9 mg
Sodium:		321 mg	Cal. from Fat:	68 %
</pre>
  </td>
