<html>
<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Mealtime Lunch Dinner
Product Mann's Vegetable Medley

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
MANNS Quick-N-Easy Chicken Vegetable Pot Pie</b></font>
<p><font color="#6A006A">






A savory pie, hot from the oven, is one of lifes better comfort foods.  There is no need to tell anyone that you know a few shortcuts to arrive at such an aromatic delight!  In fact, if you dont have leftover chicken on hand, pick up a rotisserie-cooked chicken at the supermarket. 
</font><p>



2 1/2 cups <b>Manns Vegetable Medley</b><br>
	2 cups (8 ounces) cooked chicken, coarsely chopped, skin and bones 	removed<br>
	1 1/2 cups chicken gravy, purchased or homemade<br>
	1/4 cup finely chopped onion<br>
	1/4 cup canned mushrooms, drained<br>
	2 Tablespoons heavy (whipping) cream or half-and-half<br>
	1/2 teaspoon chopped fresh thyme or 1/8 teaspoon dried thyme leaves<br>
	1 refrigerated all-ready 9-inch pie crust<br>
	Optional glaze:  1 egg yolk mixed with 1 Tablespoon cream

<p>
1. Preheat oven to 400.  In a deep-dish greased 9-inch pie plate, combine the vegetable medley, chicken, gravy, onion, mushrooms, cream and thyme, stirring to mix well.  Drape pie dough over the top, forming a decorative edge.  Cut several slits on top to vent. Brush with glaze, if desired. 
 <p>
2. Bake until filling is bubbly-hot and the crust is golden, 30 to 35 minutes.  Let cool 5 minutes before serving. 

<p>
4 Servings

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></font></u>
<pre>
Calories:	505	Vitamin A:	678 IU
Protein:	23 G	Vitamin C:	34 mg
Carbohydrates:	38 G	Thiamin:	0.3 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.6 G	Riboflavin: 	0.3 mg
