<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 15 minutes Cook 20 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Cauliflower Avocado Bake	</b></font>
<p>


1 1/2 lbs. - 1 lb. pk	<b>Manns Cauliettes&#174;</b> 
			(cauliflower florettes)<br>
1 large		Avocado, diced into 1/4" pieces<br>
1 medium		Red Bell pepper, sliced julienne<br>
1/3 cup		Green Onion, chopped<br>
1/2 cup		Bacon, cooked crisp and finely chopped<br>
1 cup 			Cheddar Cheese (medium) grated<br>
1/2 tsp.		Salt	<br>
1 tsp.			Black pepper, freshly ground<br>
2 Tbs.		Vegetable oil<br>
3 Tbs.		Fresh Parsley, finely chopped<br>
1 Tbs.		Fresh Garlic, finely minced

<p>
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 
<p>
1. Steam <b>Cauliettes</b> until tender, drain, season with salt and pepper and set aside.
 <p>
2. Saut red bell peppers over moderate heat.  When peppers soften, add green onions, garlic and parsley.  Continue to saut another two minutes.
 <p>
3. Oil a large, shallow baking pan. Place seasoned <b>Cauliettes</b> in pan, top with avocado. Spread sauted vegetables evenly over the top of the cauliettes and avocado.  Top with grated cheese.  Bake for 18-20 min.   Top with bacon and serve. 




<p>
4 - 6 Servings


  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
