<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 20 minutes Cook 15 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Herbed Brie, Spinach and Broccoli Hearts&#174; Omelet</b></font>
<p>



YIELD 2 Omelets<br>
2 Tbs.		Vegetable oil<br>
1 cup 			Yellow onion, minced<br>
1 cup 			**<b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;</b><br>
2 cups 		Manns Salad Spinach, rough chopped<br>
2 Tbs.		Fresh parsley, minced<br>
1 Tbs.		Fresh dill, minced (or 1 teaspoon of dried dill)<br>
1 Tbs.		Fresh basil, minced  (or 1/2 teaspoon of dried basil)<br>
			Salt and pepper to taste<br>
6 large		Eggs<br>
2 Tbs.		Milk<br>
2 Tbs.		Margarine<br>
1/4 lb.			Brie, thinly sliced with the rind removed



<p>
1. Heat oil in a large skillet. Add the onion and saut over moderate heat until translucent. Add 2 tablespoons of water to the skillet. Add the broccoli hearts and continue to saut until broccoli is tender
 <p>
2. Add the spinach and saut until it becomes slightly wilted. Add the prepared herbs, season with salt and pepper. Stir together and remove from heat.
 <p>
3. Combine the eggs and milk in a bowl and whisk until bubbly.
 <p>
4. Heat 1 tablespoon of margarine in a 9" non-stick skillet. When the skillet is hot, pour in half of the egg mixture. Tip the skillet so that the eggs coat the pan evenly. Keep tipping, lifting the omelets edge so that the loose eggs run underneath,. When the eggs are fairly set on top but still moist, quickly arrange half of the broccoli and spinach mixture and the Brie on one side of the omelet.
 <p>
5. Fold the omelet in half and slide it onto a plate. Repeat process for the second omelet.

<p>
** May substitute <b>Manns Cauli-Slaw&#153;</b> or <b>Manns Rainbow Slaw&#153;</b>

  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
<!--------------------------Add Above Here------------------------->
<a href="../mkrecipestoc.htm">
Back to Mom's Favorite Recipes</a>
<p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</center>
