<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 10 minutes Cook 10 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Broccoli & Carrots with Fresh Orange Sauce</b></font>
<p>


1 lb. pkg.	<b>Manns Broccoli & Carrots</b><br>
1/2 cup 	Low sodium chicken broth<br>
1/2 cup 	Orange juice, freshly-squeezed <br>
2 tsp.		Cornstarch<br>
1		Green onion, sliced<br>
1/2 tsp.	Dry basil, crushed <br>
1/2 tsp.	Sugar<br>
1/4 tsp.	Salt <br>
1/4 tsp.	Pepper<br>
1		Navel orange, peeled and thinly sliced	

<p>
1. In a pan, steam broccoli and carrots for 5 minutes, or until tender but crisp.  Transfer vegetables to plate and keep warm.
 <p>
2. In the same pan, stir together broth and juice. Add cornstarch and stir until it dissolves. Stir in onions, basil, sugar, salt, and pepper. Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until sauce begins to thicken and bubble. Cook 1 minute more.
 <p>
3. Stir in sliced orange, and add vegetables. Toss gently to coat with sauce and serve immediately.

<p>
4 Servings
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
