<font color="green"><b>
Bombay Cauliflower Rice Pilaf</b></font>
<p>



YIELD 4 - 6 Servings
<p>
2 Tbs.		Vegetable oil
<br>
3 Tbs. 		Fresh garlic, minced
<br>
3 cups 		<b>Manns Cauliettes</b>, cut into quarters
<br>
3 cups 		Brown rice, cooked
<br>
1/2 cup 		Raisins or currants
<br>
2 tsp.			Curry powder
<br>
1/2 tsp.		Ground Coriander
<br>
1/4 tsp.		Ground cinnamon
<br>
1/4 tsp.		Ground cloves
<br>
1/4 cup 		Green onions, chopped
<br>
1 Tbs.		Butter or margarine
<br>
1/2 cup 		Plain yogurt (optional)
<br>
2 Tbs.			Roasted sesame seeds


<p>
1. Saut the garlic over moderate heat for 1 minute.  Add <b>Cauliettes</b> and ginger and three tablespoons of water. Saut until the <b>Cauliettes</b> are slightly browned.
 <p>
2. Add all the remaining ingredients except the butter or margarine, yogurt and sesame seeds. Stir together and cook, covered, over very low heat for 15 minutes. Stir in the butter or margarine, yogurt (if desired) and toasted 	sesame seeds. Remove from heat and serve at once.


