  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
VEGETABLE SOUP</b></font> 
<p>


6-8 Servings<br>
Preparation Time:  15 minutes<br>
Cook Time:  25 minutes
<p>
1 tsp.		Vegetable oil<br>
1 cup 		Broccoli Wokly florettes<br>
1 cup		Carrots, chopped<br>
1 cup		Celery, sliced<br>
1/2 cup 	Onion, sliced<br>
1 can (28 oz.)	Tomatoes<br>
1/2 cup 	Parsley leaves<br>
1 clove		Fresh garlic, chopped<br>
2 cans		Chicken broth<br>
1/3 cup		Pasta<br>
2 Tbs.		Parmesan cheese, grated
<p>
Over medium heat, heat oil in a saucepan.  Add onion and garlic, cook until onion is soft (about 2-3 minutes).
<p>
Add pasta, parsley, tomatoes and chicken broth.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
<p>
Add carrots and celery, cook for 5 minutes and add broccoli, cook for an additional 10 minutes.  Add salt and pepper to taste.






