<font color="green"><b>
Smoked Ham & Spinach Quiche with Roma Tomatoes</b></font>
<p>

YIELD 6 Servings
<p>
1		10" pie crust, prepared<br>
1 oz. 		Butter or margarine<br>
2 lbs. 		Manns Salad Spinach, sauted and pureed<br>
2 Tbs.	Vegetable oil<br>
1 cup 		Onions, diced<br>
2 cups 	Smoked ham,  rough chopped (can substitute any type of ham)<br>
2 Tbs.	Fresh garlic, minced<br>
12 oz.		Light cream<br>
3 large 	Eggs<br>
1 large 	Egg yolk<br>
1/4 tsp.	Nutmeg<br>
2 oz.		Parmesan cheese, freshly grated<br>
4 ox.		Roma tomatoes, sliced

<p>
1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.  Saut onions in vegetable oil until tender.  Add the smoked ham and garlic and saut an additional 2 minutes.  Remove mixture from pan.
 <p>
2. In a bowl, beat the cream, eggs and cheese together and stir in the spinach and smoked ham mixture.  Mix all ingredients, then pour into prepared pie crust.  Arrange the Roma tomatoes slices on top, dot them with butter.  Bake for 35-40 minutes until the moisture is set and slightly browned on top.  Serve.






	


  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
