<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 15 minute Cook 50 minutes Chill 1 hour

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Wild Rice & Chicken Salad with Manns Cauli-Slaw&#174;</b></font>
<p>



2-4 Servings
<p>
1 - 14 1/2 oz can 	Chicken Broth<br>
1/2 cup 		Wild rice<br>
2 cups			Chicken, diced cooked <br>
1 cup			**<b>Manns Cauli-Slaw&#174;</b><br>
3/4 cup 		Red delicious apple, diced <br>
1			Green onion, diced
<font color="green"><b>DRESSING</b></font>
<p>
2 Tbs.		Fresh tarragon (or 2 teaspoons dried)<br>
2 1/2 Tbs.		Olive oil<br>
1 1/2 Tbs.		Cider vinegar or another type of sweet vinegar<br>
1 tsp.			Dijon mustard<br>
Salt and pepper to taste
<p>
1. Combine broth and wild rice in a small sauce pan. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer over medium-low heat until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed--about 50 minutes. Transfer to medium-size bowl,. Cover and refrigerate until well-chilled.
 <p>
2. Add chicken,<b> Manns Cauli-Slaw&#174;</b>, apple, green onion and tarragon to the wild rice.
 <p>
3. Whisk dressing ingredients together. Pour dressing over the wild rice mixture and toss well. Season with salt and pepper.
<p>
** May substitute Manns Rainbow Slaw or Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw


  </td>
  </tr>
