<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 15 minutes Chill 30 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Pasta Primavera Salad</b></font>
<p>



<img align="right" src="../../images/foodshots/PASTAPRIMAVERA.jpg">
6 Servings as an Entre<p>
1 lb. pkg.	Rotelli noodles, cooked (yields 1 1/2 lbs.)<br>
1 lb. pkg.	<b>Manns Vegetable Medley</b><br>
1/4 small	Red onion, thinly-sliced<br>
1 small	Green bell pepper,  julienne-cut <br>
2 small	Zucchini, sliced into semi-circles<br>
1 1/2 cups 	Caesar Vinaigrette dressing<p>
1. Gently toss the cooked noodles and all the vegetables in a large mixing bowl until they are blended. Pour the dressing over the noodle/vegetable mixture and toss again to thoroughly coat the mixture with dressing. 
 <p>
2. Chill for 30 minutes before serving.
<p>

<font color="green"><b>CAESAR VINAIGRETTE DRESSING</b></font>
<p>
1 cup + 2 Tbs. 	Caesar dressing, prepared (your own or favorite bottled dressing)<br>
1/4 cup + 2 Tbs. 	Vinaigrette dressing, prepared (your own or favorite bottled 				dressing)
<p>
1. Blend well. Chill until ready to use
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
