<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Lemon Rainbow Salad</b></font>
<p>

8-10 Servings<p>
2 - 1 lb. pkgs.	**<b>Manns Rainbow Salad&#153;</b><br>
1		Green bell pepper, cut into strips<br>
1		Red bell pepper, cut into strips<br>
1/2 medium	Red onion, sliced into thin strips<br>
2 tsp.		Lemon peel, grated <br>
2 Tbs.	Parsley, chopped <p>
1. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Toss to mix. Pour on dressing to taste. Toss again and serve.  Best flavor when salad has been well chilled.
<p>
<font color="green"><b>
LEMON SALAD DRESSING</b></font><br>

(Yield: Enough for 3 lbs. of <b>Rainbow Salad&#153;</b>)<br>
Chill time: 1 hour or more
<p>
1/2 cup	Mayonnaise<br>
1/4 cup 	Fresh lemon juice<br>
2 Tbs.	Olive oil<br>
1/2 cup 	Sour cream<br>
1 Tbs.	White wine vinegar<br>
1 Tbs.	Horseradish, prepared<br>
2 Tbs.	Dijon mustard<br>
2 Tbs.	Sugar<br>
2 Tbs.	Corn syrup<br>
1 tsp.		Salt<br>
1/2 tsp.	Pepper<br>
1/2 tsp.	Celery seeds<p>
1. Combine all ingredients by whisking them together in a bowl. Refrigerate dressing until well chilled.  Dressing may be prepared 1 day ahead.
<p>
** May substitute <b>Manns Cauli-Slaw&#153;</b> or <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw&#174;</b>

