<font color="green"><b>
 Broccoli Spaghetti Parmesana</b></font>
<p>




YIELD 4-6 Servings	
<p>
2 -1lb. pkgs.	 	<b>Broccoli Wokly florettes</b>, coarsely chopped<br>
1/2 tsp.		Garlic salt<br>
2 Tbs.		Olive oil<br>
1 -1lb. 	pkg	 	Spaghetti (or any style you prefer)<br>
1/2 cup		Butter or margarine<br>
2-3 Cloves		Garlic, crushed
<p>
1. Bring water and garlic salt to boil in a pot and cook spaghetti according to the directions on the spaghetti package.  5 minutes before spaghetti is done cooking, add the <b>Broccoli Wokly</b>.  Drain
 <p.
 
2. Place spaghetti and broccoli in a large bowl and toss with olive oil, butter,  and garlic.  Salt and pepper to taste.  May be served hot or cold.
<p>
*Note Garlic may always be increased depending on personal preference. 

