<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 15 minutes Cook 10 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Bratwurst and Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b></font>
<p>





YIELD 4 Servings<p>
4 cups 	**<b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>.<br>
1 cup 		Cabbage, shredded<br>
2 cups 	Red (or yellow) delicious apples, diced <br>
2 tsp.		Fresh Garlic,  finely chopped <br>
2 Tbs.	Olive oil<br>
1/4 cup 	Alsatian white wine (Riesling or Gewurtztraminer)<br>
Salt and pepper to taste<br>
1/2 cup	Your favorite poppy seed dressing
<p>
1. Pour olive oil into preheated large frying pan. Add Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw, red cabbage and apples. Saut until vegetables are tender but still slightly crisp.
 <p>
2. Add garlic, wine, and spices. Continue to saut until wine has evaporated. Add poppy seed dressing. Stir vegetables to keep them tender but crisp.
 <p>
3. Serve with Bratwurst or your favorite sausage as an entre or as a sandwich in a large French roll with spicy mustard.

<p>
**May substitute <b.Manns Cauli-SlawTM</b> or <b>Manns Rainbow SaladTM</b>

  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
