<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>



<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 40 minutes Cook 40 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Marlenes Broccoli Cole Slaw Enchiladas</b></font>
<p>



YIELD 12 Servings (1 each) or 6 Servings (2 each)
<p>
1 Tbs.			Olive oil<br>
1 -1 lb. pkg. 		<b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b><br>
1 medium 		Yellow or white onion, diced<br>
3/4 clove 		Fresh garlic, minced<br>
1/2 cup 		Pace Picante Sauce, Thick & Chunky, Mediumv
1 -1/4 oz. pkg. 	Taco seasoning (mix per instructions on pouch)<br>
8 oz.			Cheddar cheese  (medium) shredded
			(low fat is O.K.)<br>

8  oz.			Monterey Jack cheese  shredded
			(low fat is O.K.)<br>
1 -28 ounce can 	Las Palmas Enchilada Sauce<br>
1 cup			Pace Picante Sauce (mild or medium)<br>
1  -5 3/4 oz. can 	Olives, drained, ripe, pitted and broken <br>
1 - 2 1/4 oz. can 	Olives, drained, ripe and sliced <br>
12 			Flour tortillas (7" size)<p>
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
<p>
2. In large (6 quart) saucepan, put olive oil, <b>Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw</b>, diced onions, minced garlic, 1/2 cup of Pace Picante Sauce. Mix well and cook, covered, over medium heat about 10-12 minutes, stirring 3 or 4 times. 
<p>
3. Add taco seasoning and mix well. Cook another 5-8 minutes, covered. Add all of the olives, mix, and then set aside.
<p>
4. Mix the 2 cheeses in a bowl.<p>
5. To Assemble:  Pour about 1 cup of the Las Palmas Enchilada Sauce into a 8 or 9" pie plate, reserving the rest,. Dip tortillas one at a time, covering both sides with sauce. Divide the cole slaw mixture into 12 portions and the cheese into 12 portions. Fill each tortilla and place seam down in a greased 11" x 16" x 3" pan. Mix remaining enchilada sauce and 1 cup of Pace Picante Sauce and pour over top of enchiladas covering completely. Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake on the middle rack of oven for 40 minutes. Garnish with sour cream, guacamole and additional Pace Picante Sauce.
<p>
6. This dish can be prepared ahead of time and frozen.  When ready to cook simply place in oven and cook. 

  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
