  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Marinated Vegetable Salad</b></font>
<p>



Serves 12

<p>
1		can (14 1/2 oz.) Swanson ready-to-serve clear vegetable broth<br>
1		Tablespoon of sugar<br>
1/2	teaspoon crushed dried thyme leaves<br>
1/4	teaspoon of garlic powder or 2 cloves of garlic, minced<br>
1/8	teaspoon of pepper<br>
1		bag of <b>Manns Cauliettes&#174; </b><br>
1/2	lb. of green beans cut into 1" pieces<br>
2		medium carrots, sliced<br>
1/4	cup of vinegar<br>
2	Tablespoons of chopped fresh parsley pr 2 teaspoons of dried parsley flakes
<p>
1.	In a saucepan, mix broth, sugar, thyme, garlic powder, pepper, cauliflower, 	green beans and carrots. Bring to a boil over high heat.
<p>2.	Cover and cook over low heat for 1 minute or until vegetables are tender-crisp. 	Add vinegar and parsley.
<p>3.	Spoon mixture into large, shallow serving dish. Refrigerate at least 12 hours.


