<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>



<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 10 minutes Cook 30 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Risotto Verdee</b></font>
<p>




Serves 4
<p>
1		Tablespoon of margarine or butter<br>
4 		green onions, sliced<br>
1/4	cup chopped celery<br>
1		cup of uncooked, regular long-grain rice<br>
1		can (10 1/2 oz.) of Campbells condensed chicken or beef broth<br>
1		soup can of water<br>
		2 cups of <b>Manns Salad Spinach</b><br>
3 		Tablespoons of grated Parmesan cheese<br>
<p>
1. Heat margarine in a skillet over medium heat. Add onions and celery and cook until tender-crisp.<p>
2. Add rice and cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Stir in broth, water and spinach. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until the rice is done.<p>
3. Stir in cheese and serve.



  </td>
  </tr>
