<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Vegetable Rotini</b></font>
<p>

Serves 6
<p>
2 1/2 cups of dry, corkscrew macaroni<br>
4 		cups of<b> Manns Broccoli & Carrots</b><br>
1		package  (3 oz.) of softened cream cheese or cream cheese with chives<br>
1		can (10 1/4 oz.) of Campbells condensed broccoli cheese soup.<br>
3/4	cup of milk<br>
2 		Tablespoons of Dijon-style mustard (optional)<br>
1/2 	cup of grated Parmesan cheese<br>
1/8	teaspoon of pepper
<p>
1. In a saucepan, prepare macaroni according to directions of the package. Add broccoli and carrots for the last 5 minutes of cooking. Drain in a colander
<p>
2. In the same pan, stir cream cheese until smooth. (to soften, remove cream cheese from wrapper, place on microwave-safe plate and microwave on high for 10 seconds) Stir in soup, milk, mustard, Parmesan cheese and pepper. Heat through over low heat. Add macaroni and vegetables. Heat thoroughly. Serve.
 



