<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>



<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 10 minutes Cook 25 minutes 
Kids

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Skillet Chicken & Broccoli Wokly </b></font>
<p>


Serves 4
<p>
1	Tablespoon of margarine or butter<br>
4	skinless, boneless chicken breast halves<br>
1	can (10 1/4 oz.) Campbells condensed broccoli cheese soup<br>
1/3	cup of water or milk<br>
1/8	teaspoon of pepper<br>
2 	cups of <b>Manns Broccoli Wokly</b>	
<p>
1. In a skillet, heat margarine over medium-high heat. Cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned. Set chicken aside.
<p>
2. Add soup, water, pepper and broccoli. Heat to a boil. Return chicken to pan. Cover and cook over low heart 10 minutes or until the chicken is no longer pink.





