<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 20 minutes Cook 20 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Oriental Chicken & Vegetables </b></font>
<p>



Serves 4
<p>
2	 	Tablespoons of cornstarch<br>
1 		can (14 1/2 oz.) of Swanson ready to serve clear chicken broth.<br>
1 		Tablespoon of soy sauce<br>
2 		Tablespoons of vegetable oil<br>
1		lb. of skinless, boneless chicken breasts cuts into strips<br>
1		bag (16 oz.) of <b>Manns Broccoli Wokly</b> Stir Fry<br>
1/4	teaspoon of ground ginger<br>
1/8	teaspoon of garlic powder or 1 glove of garlic, minced<br>
4		cups of cooked rice
<p>
1. Mix cornstarch. broth, and soy until smooth. Set aside. In a skillet, heat half the oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken in 2 batches and stir-fry until browned. Set chicken aside.
<p>
2. Add remaining oil. Add vegetables, ginger, and garlic powder. Stir-fry over medium heat until tender-crisp.
<p>
3. Stir cornstarch mixture and add. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Return chicken to pan. Heat through. Serve over rice.


  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
