<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/26/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/26/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Prep 15 minutes cook 25 minutes 
Kids

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" link="green" vlink="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<a name=top>
<!---------------------Add Below Here---------------------->
 

<table width="600" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolordark="#FFEBD7" bordercolorlight="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica" size="3">

<font color="green"><b>
Beef & Broccoli </b></font>
<p>





Serves 4
<p>
1	lb. of boneless beef sirloin or top round steak 3/4" thick<br>
2	Tablespoons cornstarch<br>
1	can (14 1/2 oz.) Swanson ready-to-serve clear beef broth<br>
1	Tablespoon of packed brown sugar<br>
1	Tablespoon of soy sauce<br>
Vegetable cooking spray<br>
1/4	teaspoon of garlic powder<br>
1/4	teaspoon of ground ginger<br>
4	cups of<b> Manns Broccoli Wokly</b><br>
4	cups of hot cooked rice
<p>
1. Slice beef into very thin strips. Mix cornstarch, 1 cup of broth, brown sugar and soy until smooth. Set aside.
<p>
2. Spray skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat 1 minute. Add beef in 2 batches and stir fry until brown. Set beef aside.
<p>
3. Add remaining broth, garlic powder, ginger and broccoli. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.

Stir cornstarch mixture and add. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Return beef to pan. Heat through. Serve over rice.
 

  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
<!--------------------------Add Above Here------------------------->
<a href="../mkrecipestoc.htm">
Back to Mom's Favorite Recipes</a>
<p>
</td>
</tr>
