<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Mealtime Lunch Dinner 
Region New Orleans 
Product Mann's Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry 
Prep time 3 4 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Raging Cajun Stir Fry
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Raging Cajun Stir Fry
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (4 oz.) Servings 	</b></nobr><br>
	50 oz.	<br>
	3 oz.	<br>
	32 oz./1 quart	<br>
	4 oz.	<br>
	25 lbs.	

   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Chicken or vegetable broth<br>
Cajun seasonings<br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Minced garlic<br>
Manns Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry

   </td>
	


   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large measuring pitcher, combine broth and Cajun seasonings; stir to blend.
 <p>
2. For individual service:  heat 2 tsp. vegetable oil in wok, skillet or on flat grill.  Add 1/4 tsp. garlic and 4 oz. (1 cup) Stir Fry Vegetables and cook for 2 minutes while tossing vegetables until broccoli turns bright green.
 <p>
3. Add 1 Tbs. Cajun spiced broth and continue to stir fry another 30 to 60 seconds until vegetables are glazed, but still crisp, and liquid has evaporated.




<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	129	Vitamin A:	876 IU
Protein:	3.3 G	Vitamin C:	56 mg
Carbohydrates:	9.4 G	Thiamin:	0.08 mg
Dietary Fiber:	3.4 G	Riboflavin:	0.1 mg
Fat-total:	9.5 G	Niacin:		1 mg
Saturated fat	1.3 G	Calcium:	46 mg
Cholesterol:	0.7 mg	Iron:		1 mg
Sodium:		234 mg	Cal. from Fat:	62 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
