<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Mealtime Dinner
Region Lyon France
Entertaining Bastille Day July 14th 
Product Mann's Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry 
Prep time 6 8 minutes 

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry with Red Wine
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry with Red Wine
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (10 oz.) Servings 	</b></nobr><br>
	6.25 quarts 	<br>
	50 oz.	<br>
	1/2 cup	<br>
	50 oz.	<br>
	18.75 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
	25 lbs.<br>	
	6.25 lbs.	

   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Prepared beef gravy<br>
Dry red wine<br>
Dried thyme leaves<br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Skirt, flank or other beef steak,<br>
		thinly sliced<br>
Manns Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry<br>
Sliced mushrooms
   </td>
	



   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In a large container, combine gravy, wine and thyme.
 <p>
2. For individual service:  Heat 1 Tbs. oil in a wok, skillet or on flat grill, add 3 oz. of beef and cook while stirring for 30 seconds.  Add Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry Vegetables and mushrooms and cook for another 30 to 60 seconds while continuing to toss mixture.  Add 2-1/2 oz. gravy mixture and stir fry another 30 seconds to heated through.
 <p>
3. For volume feeding:  Fill steam table pans with stir fry mixture and serve on-line.
<p></font>
<i>Note:  Vegetable Stir Fry Francais is perfect for serving over mashed potatoes or steamed rice.</i>
<font face="Helvetica">






<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	405	Vitamin A:	853 IU
Protein:	35 G	Vitamin C:	56 mg
Carbohydrates:	10 G	Thiamin:	0.6 mg
Dietary Fiber:	3.4 G	Riboflavin: 	0.3 mg
Fat-total:	23 G	Niacin:		4.7 mg
Saturated fat	5.6 G	Calcium:	54 mg
Cholesterol:	50 mg	Iron:		3.8 mg
Sodium:		466 mg	Cal. from Fat:	52 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
