<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Mealtime-Lunch/Dinner 
Region (Mexicali, Mexico) 
Kids 
Entertaining-Cinco de Mayo 
Product--Mann's Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry 
Prep time 6-8 minutes 

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->



<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Mexicali Stir Fry
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Mexicali Stir Fry
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (12 oz.) Servings 	</b></nobr><br>
	50 oz.	<br>
	18.75 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
	25 lbs.	<br>
	3 gallons	<br>
-<br>
	6.25 lbs.	<br>
	6.25 lbs.	

   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Boneless, skinless chicken breast,<br>
		cut into 3/4-inch pieces<br>
Manns Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry<br>
Canned red chile sauce or<br>
		enchilada  sauce<br>
Frozen, cut corn<br>
Diced tomatoes (fresh or canned)
   </td>
	





   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. <u>Per order</u>:  Heat 1 Tbs. oil in wok, skillet or on flat grill.  Add 3 oz. of chicken and cook while stirring for 1 minute or until meat begins to turn opaque.  
 <p>
2. Add 4 oz. (1 cup) Broccoli Wokly Stir Fry Vegetables and cook for another 30 to 60 seconds while continuing to toss mixture.  
 <p>
3. Add 5 oz. red chile sauce and 1 ounce each, corn and tomato; stir fry another minute until heated through and sauce thickens.  If desired, serve with warm corn bread, polenta cakes or Spanish rice.




<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	367	Vitamin A:	1169 IU
Protein:	30 G	Vitamin C:	63 mg
Carbohydrates:	19 G	Thiamin:	0.2 mg
Dietary Fiber:	5.5 G	Riboflavin: 	0.3 mg
Fat-total:	18 G	Niacin:		13 mg
Saturated fat	3 G	Calcium:	67 mg
Cholesterol:	73 mg	Iron:		2.3 mg
Sodium:		717 mg	Cal. from Fat:	45 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
