<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Mealtime Lunch Dinner 
Product Mann's Vegetable Medley

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 QUICK-N-EASY CHICKEN & VEGETABLE POT PIE
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS QUICK-N-EASY CHICKEN & VEGETABLE POT PIE

</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (6 oz.) Servings 	</b></nobr><br>
	12.5 lbs.	<br>
	12.5 lbs.	<br>
	-<br>

	9.25 quarts	<br>
	1.5 lbs.<br>
	1.5 lbs.	<br>
	4 oz.	<br>
	1 Tbs.	<br>
	12 lbs.	
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Vegetables Medley<br>
Cooked, boneless, skinless chicken,<br>
cut into 1/2-inch chunks<br>
Prepared chicken gravy<br>
Chopped yellow onion<br>
Sliced mushrooms<br>
Heavy cream<br>
Dried thyme leaves<br>
Prepared pie dough, rolled into<br>
		sheets and chilled
   </td>
	

   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large container, combine Vegetable Medley, chicken, gravy, onion, mushrooms, cream and thyme; toss to combine ingredients.
 <p>
2. Pour chicken and vegetable mixture into hotel pans and top with sheets of pastry dough.  Cut vents in dough to vent steam.  Score pastry into squares before baking to mark servings and control portion size.
 <p>
3. Bake at 400F for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly-hot.

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	505	Vitamin A:	678 IU
Protein:	23 G	Vitamin C:	34 mg
Carbohydrates:	38 G	Thiamin:	0.3 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.6 G	Riboflavin: 	0.3 mg
Fat-total:	29 G	Niacin:		8.3 mg
Saturated fat	8.4 G	Calcium:	85 mg
Cholesterol:	62 mg	Iron:		2.8 mg
Sodium:		982 mg	Cal. from Fat:	52 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
