<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Mother Of All Hashes</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Mother Of All Hashes</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (3 oz.) Servings </b></nobr><br>
	 6 lbs.	<br>
	7.5 lbs.	<br>
        
	3.75 lbs.	<br>
	2.5 lbs.	<br>
	2 lbs.	 
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Prepared, seasoned mashed potatoes<br>
Frozen, diced red potatoes<br>
Diced turkey ham<br>
Low-fat, sharp cheddar cheese, shredded
   </td>
   <td valign="top">
  
  </td>
   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>
<img align="right" src="../../images/foodshots/hash.jpeg">
<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large container, combine Broccoli Cole Slaw with mashed potatoes, diced potatoes and turkey ham.
 <p>
2. Spoon mixture into 2 full-size hotel pans, smooth into even layer. Sprinkle with cheese.
 <p>
3. Bake at 350F for 30 to 40 minutes until heated through.
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font>
<pre>
Calories:	90	Vitamin A:	121 IU
Protein:	6.8 G	Vitamin C:	26 mg
