<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Food Service Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/1/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 10/15/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
  Spicy Buffalo Potato Skins

</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Spicy Buffalo Potato Skins

</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	100 (2-ounce) count	<br> 
	1.5 lbs./24 oz.<br>
	12 oz.	<br>
	6.25 lbs.	<br>
	50 oz.	
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Frozen potato skins, thawed<br>
	Butter, melted<br>
Louisiana-style hot sauce<br>
Manns Broccoli & Cauliflower <br>
Prepared blue cheese dressing
   </td>
	

   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. On large sheet pan, arrange potato skins cut side up.
 <p>
2. In large bowl, combine butter and hot sauce; stir to blend.
 <p>
3. Add Broccoli and Cauliflower to sauce and toss to coat.
 <p>
4. Fill each potato shell with 1 ounce of seasoned vegetables. Drizzle any remaining sauce over filled potato skins.
 <p>
5. Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 375F for 12 to 15 minutes, until potato skins are crisp and vegetables are cooked but still tender.
 <p>
6. Top each hot potato skin and vegetables with a Tbs. of blue cheese dressing and serve immediately.

 
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	240	Vitamin A:	106 IU
Protein:	4 G	Vitamin C:	37 mg
Carbohydrates:	29 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	4.7 G	Riboflavin: 	0.1 mg
Fat-total:	13.1 G	Niacin:		2 mg
Saturated fat	4.9 G	Calcium:	46 mg
Cholesterol:	23.2 mg	Iron:		4 mg
Sodium:		244 mg	Cal. from Fat:	47 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
