<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli
Mealtime Snack Appetizer Lunch Dinner 
Region Japan
Entertaining Hors d'oeurves Asian theme dinners 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
Prep time 10 minutes 

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font size="7" face="Helvetica" color="#6A006A">
Crispy-Asian Broccoli Patties</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------------#3------------------------->
 
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font color="green" face="Helvetica"><b>
MANNS Crispy-Asian Broccoli Patties</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
   <td>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<b><nobr>100 (4 oz.) Servings </nobr></b><br>
	15 lbs.	<br>
        -<br>
	2.5 quarts/40 eggs	<br>
	5 cups	<br>
	20 oz.	<br>
	36 oz.	
	
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Eggs, lightly beaten<br>
Flour<br>
Prepared teriyaki glaze<br>
Vegetable oil, divided

   </td>
   <td valign="top">
  <img src="../../images/foodshots/asian_patties.jpeg">
  </td>
   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>


<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large container, combine Broccoli Cole Slaw with eggs, flour, teriyaki glaze and 20 oz. vegetable oil.  Can chill mixture up to 3 hours before cooking.
 <p>
2. Cook to order, heat 1 tsp. oil on flat grill; add two 1/4 cup (2 ounce) scoops of broccoli batter  to form two patties.
 <p>
3. Cook, turning once, until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</u></b></font><pre>
Calories:	164	Vitamin A:	314 IU
Protein:	5 G	Vitamin C:	55 mg
Carbohydrates:	10 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2 G	Riboflavin: 	0.2 mg
Fat-total:	12 G	Niacin:	        0.7 mg
Saturated fat	1.9 G	Calcium:	44 mg
Cholesterol:	85 mg	Iron:	        1 mg
Sodium:	        163 mg	Cal. from Fat:	65 %
</pre>

  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
