<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Breakfast Lunch Dinner 
Region California
Entertaining Brunches 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
Prep time 13 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font size="7" face="Helvetica" color="#6A006A">
California Broccoli Home Fries</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!-----------------------------#1--------------------------------->
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td>
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS California Broccoli Home Fries</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
   <td>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<b>100 (3 oz.) Servings </b><br>
	7.5 lbs.	<br>
	7.5 lbs.	<br>
        -<br>
	5 lbs.	<br>
	5 lbs.	<br>
	2 cups	<br>
	As needed	
   </td>
 
   <td>
<font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Frozen, diced red potatoes, thawed<br>
Chopped onion<br>
Diced red and green bell peppers<br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Salt and pepper
   </td>
   </tr>
   </table>
</center>
 <font face="Helvetica">
<p>
<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large container, combine Broccoli Cole Slaw with potatoes, onions and peppers; toss to mix well.  Can be covered and chilled until service.
 <p>
2. Cook to order:  Heat 1 tsp. oil on flat grill, add 4 oz. (1 cup) home fry mixture; season with salt and pepper and cook for 2 to 3 minutes while tossing mixture on grill.
 <p>
3. Serve immediately alongside eggs, sandwiches, burgers or use as a filling in breakfast burritos.
 <p>

<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving </b></u></font>
<pre>
Calories:	90	Vitamin A:	172 IU
Protein:	2 G	Vitamin C:	49 mg
Carbohydrates:	11.5 G	Thiamin:	0.08 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.3 G	Riboflavin: 	0.05 mg
Fat-total:	4.5 G	Niacin:	        0.8 mg
Saturated fat	0.6 G	Calcium:	25 mg
Cholesterol:	0 mg	Iron:	        0.7 mg
Sodium:	        11 mg	Cal. from Fat:	43 %
 </pre>

  </td>
