<html>
<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Food Service Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/1/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 10/15/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Snack Lunch Dinner 
Region China Mexico 
Entertaining Cookouts Kids Birthday Parties 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 Asian Brocco Burrito</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Asian Brocco Burrito</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 Servings </b></nobr><br>
	12.5 lbs.	<br>
	1.5 lbs.	<br>
	4 oz.	<br>
	1 cup	<br>
	12.5 lbs. <br>	
	6.25 lbs.	<br>
	5 cups	<br>
	2 Tbs.	<br>
	100	<br>
	6.25 quarts	

   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Diced onions<br>
Minced garlic<br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Ground turkey, cooked<br>
Shredded Jack cheese<br>
Szechwan spicy stir fry sauce<br>
Chinese 5-spice powder<br>
Flour tortillas 
		(9 or 10-Inch)<br>
Plum sauce
   </td>
  

 
   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large container, combine Broccoli Cole Slaw, onion and garlic.  
<p>
2. In large skillet, wok or over flat grill, heat 1/4 cup vegetable oil, 	divide vegetables into fourths and stir fry each batch until tender, about 2 minutes.  
<p>
3. Toss cooked vegetables with cooked ground turkey, cheese, stir fry sauce and 5-spice powder until mixed thoroughly.  
<p>
4. <u>For individual service</u>: Chill filling until ready to use.  To assemble burrito, warm tortilla on flat grill and heat 3/4 cup of burrito filling.  Place 3/4 cup warm burrito filling down the center of tortilla, fold in the left and right side of tortilla over filling and roll burrito away from you to close.  Serve immediately with 2 oz. plum sauce on the side.
<p>
5. <u>For volume feeding</u>: Follow steps 1 - 3, assemble 100 burritos as described above and wrap burritos in paper or foil.  Burritos can be held in a warming bin or steam table.<br></font>
<i>Note:  Burritos can be made into Chimichangas  by deep frying rolled burritos until golden, about 3 to 4 minutes.</i>
<font face="Helvetica">

 
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	404	Vitamin A:	310 IU
Protein:	28 G	Vitamin C:	48 mg
Carbohydrates:	26 G	Thiamin:	0.3 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.1 G	Riboflavin: 	0.4 mg
Fat-total:	21 G	Niacin:		4.4 mg
Saturated fat	8 G	Calcium:	304 mg
Cholesterol:	83 mg	Iron:		3.1 mg
Sodium:		734 mg	Cal. from Fat:	47 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
