Prepared Alfredo or <br>
		Parmesan cream sauce<br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Frozen peas<br>
Dry spaghetti, cooked and
		drained<br>
Grated Parmesan cheese
   </td>
  
	 
   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large stock pot, combine sauce with Broccoli Cole Slaw and peas.  Cook over low heat until heated through.
 <p>
2. Per order:  Toss 1-1/2 cups warm pasta with 2/3 cup broccoli-sauce and top with 1 Tbs. Parmesan cheese.  For volume feeding:  Toss broccoli-sauce with warm pasta, pour mixture into steam table pans and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.


 
<p>
