<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Food Service Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/1/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/30/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Lunch Supper 
Entertaining Cookouts Kids Birthday Parties Vegetarian Feasts 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Crunchy Brocco-Burger</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Crunchy Brocco-Burger</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (4 oz.) Servings </b></nobr><br>
	10 lbs.	<br>
	5 lbs.	<br>
	3.5 lbs.	<br>
	1.75 lbs	<br>
	1.75 lbs.	<br>
	60 oz.	<br>
	1-1/8 cups	
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Cooked brown rice<br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Canned kidney beans, drained<br>
Sliced mushrooms<br>
Grated Parmesan cheese<br>
Egg whites<br>
Taco seasoning blend
   </td>
  
   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In large container, combine rice, Broccoli Cole Slaw, beans, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, egg whites and seasoning; toss to blend.
 <p>
2. In food processor, blend burger mixture in batches until finely chopped and ingredients are combined.
 <p>
3. Using a 4-ounce scoop, portion burgers and place on a lightly oil sheet pans.  Flatten scoops with spatula to form patties.
 <p>
4. Bake burgers at 500F until browned, about 10 minutes.  Burgers can be cooked in advance and re-heated in steam table pans, toaster or oven.  Burgers can also be cooked on an oiled grill for 3 to 4 minutes per side.  Serve on whole wheat buns with lettuce, onion, pickles or salsa.


 
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font>
<pre>
Calories:	126	Vitamin A:	110 IU
Protein:	8.3 G	Vitamin C:	19 mg
Carbohydrates:	17 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.4 G	Riboflavin: 	0.2 mg
Fat-total:	2.9 G	Niacin:		1.4 mg
Saturated fat	1.6 G	Calcium:	130 mg
Cholesterol:	6.3 mg	Iron:		0.8 mg
Sodium:		444 mg	Cal. from Fat:	21 %
 </pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
