<title>Mann's Broccoli Food Service Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/1/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 10/15/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>


<!-----------------------------Keywords------------------------->

<!--

Unbelievable Broccoli 
Mealtime Lunch Supper 
Entertaining Cookouts Kids Parties Picnics Cinco de Mayo 
Product Mann's Broccoli Cole Slaw 
Prep time 10 minutes

-->

<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 MANNS Brocco Taco Salad


</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Brocco Taco Salad

</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>

<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
	
	12.5 lbs	<br>
	12.5 lbs.	<br>
	4 1/2 lbs. (3 qts.)	<br>
	3 lbs.	<br>
	3 lbs.	<br>
	3/4 lb.	<br>
	3/4 lb.	<br>
	1 1/2 qts.	<br>
	24 oz.	<br>
	3 lbs.	<br>
	As needed	
   </td>

   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Ground beef or turkey, cooked<br>
Red kidney beans, drained<br>
Cheddar cheese, shredded<br>
Tomatoes, diced<br>
Red onion, chopped<br>
Black olives, sliced<br>
Thousand Island salad dressing<br>
Salsa<br>
Corn chips or tortilla chips<br>
Salt and pepper
   </td>




   </tr>
   </table>
</center>
<font face="Helvetica">
<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Combine Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw, ground beef, kidney beans, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, onions and olives, tossing to mix well.  Add salad dressing and salsa.  Season to taste.
 <p>
2. Just before serving, stir in corn chips.  Alternatively, each salad can be garnished with about 1 1/2 cups ( 1 1/4 oz.) corn chips.
 <p>
3. Optional:  For authentic Mexican flavor, salad dressing may be omitted from recipe, and onions may be cooked with ground beef/turkey.  
 
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
