<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Honey-Glazed Vegetable Medley
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
Honey-Glazed Vegetable Medley
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>100 (2 1/2 oz.) Servings 	</b></nobr><br>
	12 oz./1-1/2 cups 	<br>
	8 oz./1 cup	<br>
	4 oz./1/2 cup	<br>
	4 oz./1/2 cup	<br>
	4 tsp. 	<br>
	2 tsp. 	<br>
	12 lbs.	<br>
	8 lbs. 	
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Honey<br>
Dijon mustard<br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Chicken broth or water<br>
Salt<br>
Ground black pepper<br>
Manns Vegetable Medley<br>
Russet potatoes, unpeeled, cut<br>
		into 3/4-inch chunks

   </td>

	




   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Combine honey, mustard, oil, chicken broth or water, salt, and pepper.
 <p>
2. Evenly distribute broccoli, carrots and potatoes in hotel pans, toss with honey mixture to coat.  
 <p>
3. Bake at 400F, stirring once or twice, until potatoes are tender and other vegetables are browned at the edges, about 40 to 45 minutes.


<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	90	Vitamin A:	840 IU
Protein:	2 G	Vitamin C:	34 mg
Carbohydrates:	18 G	Thiamin:	0.1 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.6 G	Riboflavin: 	0.1 mg
Fat-total:	1.4 G	Niacin:		1.1 
Saturated fat	0.2 G	Calcium:	28 mg
Cholesterol:	0 mg	Iron:		1 mg
Sodium:		146 mg	Cal. from Fat:	13 %
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
