<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Manns Chinese Chicken Salad
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
Manns Chinese Chicken Salad
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>6-8 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
	3 lbs.	<br>
1 lb.	<br>	
1 1/2 lbs.	<br>
1 lb.	<br>
1 lb.	<br>
-<br>
4 oz.	<br>
-<br>
4 oz.	<br>
3 cups	<br>
3 oz.	
   </td>




<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<b>50 Servings	</b><br>
15 lbs.	<br>
8 lbs.<br>
9 lbs.	<br>
8 lbs.	<br>
8 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
1 1/2 lbs.<br>	
-<br>
1 1/2 lbs.	<br>
4 qts.	<br>
10 oz.	
   </td>

   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Soba Noodles, cooked and well drained<br>
Chicken breast, cut into julienne strips<br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Manns Broccoli Wokly<br>
Cucumber, peeled, seeded and cut into<br>
		semi circles<br>
Red Bell Pepper, seeded, cut into 1"<br>
		julienne strips<br>
Green onions, tops only, cut on bias 1" long<br>
Oriental dressing (see notes below)<br>
Peanuts, (plain, unsalted or roasted)
   </td>






   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Place cooked, chilled noodles and all of the vegetables in a suitable size mixing bowl. Gently toss the ingredients to thoroughly blend together.
 <p>
2. Pour the dressing over the salad ingredients and gently toss together, evenly 
 <p>
3. Allow the salad to chill for 1 hour prior to serving.
 <p>
4. Prior to serving, sprinkle 1 tablespoon of peanuts over each salad.
<p>
<b><font color="green">Oriental Dressing:</b></font><br>
1. Using a prepared Oriental Dressing of your choice, the following procedure and ingredients are optional
 <p>
2. To prepare one quart of dressing, mix 1 quart of your favorite Oriental Dressing with 1/2 cup of fresh chopped cilantro and 2 tablespoons of chile garlic paste.
 <p>
3. Blend dressing thoroughly, obtaining a finished dressing of uniform color and consistency.




<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	1523
Protein:	38.2 G
Carbohydrate:	119 G
Dietary Fiber:	13.1 G
Fat Total:	114 G
Cholesterol:	47.8 mg
Sodium:		1549 mg
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
