<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 Chinese Cold Sesame Noodle Salad
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
Manns Chinese Cold Sesame Noodle Salad
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>48 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
	1 qt.	<br>
	2 cups	<br>
	1/2 cup	<br>
	1/2 cup	<br>
	1/4 cup	<br>
	2 1/2 Tbs.	<br>
	4 tsp.	<br>
	1/2 cup	<br>
	1/2 cup	<br>
	2 1/2 Tbs.	<br>
	8 lbs.	<br>
	12 lbs.<br>	
-<br>
	2 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
	1 lb.	<br>
-
   </td>

   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Peanut Butter, chunky style<br>
Soy sauce<br>
Red wine vinegar<br>
Brown Sugar<br>
Garlic, crushed<br>
Ginger root, freshly grated<br>
Salt<br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Asian Sesame Oil<br>
Asian Hot Chile Oil<br>
Spaghettini, cooked<br>
Manns Broccoli Florettes, <br>
		blanched, drained and cooled<br>
Red Bell Pepper, cut into thin <br>
		strips<br>
Scallions, thinly sliced<br>
		Toasted sesame seeds (optional)

   </td>
	








   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Combine peanut butter, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, garlic, ginger, salt, vegetable oil, sesame oil and hot chili until well blended.
 <p>
2. Toss with spaghettini, broccoli, red bell peppers and scallions to coat well.
 <p>
3. Chill until ready to serve.
 <p>
4. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds as desired.
 
 



<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	373
Protein:	15.8 G
Carbohydrate:	48.2 G
Dietary Fiber:	9.1 G
Fat-Total:	16.1 G
Cholesterol:	0 mg
Sodium:		1279 mg
</pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
