<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
  Broccoli Pizza
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="2">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Broccoli Pizza
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>48 Servings	</b></nobr><br>

(2 sheet pans)	<br>
1/2 cup	<br>
5 lbs.	<br>
2 lbs.	<br>
1 1/2 qts.<br>	
1 1/4 lbs.	<br>
6 oz.	<br>
2 lbs.	
</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>96 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
	(4 sheet pans)	<br>
1 cup	<br>
10 lbs.	<br>
4 lbs.	<br>
3 qts.	<br>
2 1/2 lbs.	<br>
12 oz.	<br>
4 lbs.	
   </td>
   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
-<br>
Yellow Cornmeal<br>
Prepared pizza dough*<br>
Manns Pizza-cut Broccoli Florettes**<br>
Prepared pizza sauce<br>
Fresh mushrooms, sliced 1/8"<br>
Green onions, sliced 1/4"<br>
Part-skim mozzarella cheese, shredded

   </td>

   </tr>
   </table>

</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. For each full sheet pan pizza: Sprinkle 1/4 cup cornmeal on sheet pan.  Roll 1/2 pounds pizza dough to fit pan.  Bake at 425_ F for 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
<p>
2. Steam broccoli until tender-crisp, according to package directions.  Set aside. Refrigerate until ready to assemble pizzas.
<p>
3. Spread crust with 3 cups sauce; sprinkle with 10 ounces of mushrooms, 1 pound broccoli, 3 ounces green onions and 1 pound of cheese.  Return to the oven and bake for 10 additional minutes or until hot and cheese is bubbly.  Cut each pizza 4" x 6" to make 24 servings per pan.
<p><i>
* Alternately, use 6 or 12 par-baked 17-inch round pizza shells for 48 or 96 servings.  Steam broccoli according to step 2.  To assemble, spread each shell with 1 cup sauce; sprinkle with 3.3. oz. mushrooms, 5 oz. of broccoli, 1 oz. green onions and 5 oz. cheese.  Cook as directed.  Cut each shell into 8 servings.
<p>
** Alternately, use Manns Broccoli Wokly or Manns Gourmet Broccoli Florettes. After steaming, cut florettes into 1-inch or less pieces.
</i>
<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	200
Protein:	10 G
Carbohydrate:	27 G
Dietary Fiber:	1 G
Fat-total:	5 G
Cholesterol:	10 mg
Sodium:		400 mg
Cal. from fat:	21%
</pre>

<p><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Quantities/Procedures for Individual Pizzas:</b>
<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">

1/2 tsp.	<br>
2 1/2 oz.	<br>
1/3 cup	<br>
1/2 oz.	<br>
1 1/2 oz.	<br>
1/4 oz.<br>
1 1/2 oz. 
</td>	
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	Yellow Corn Meal<br>
Prepared pizza dough<br>
Prepared pizza sauce<br>
Sliced mushrooms<br>
Manns Pizza-cut Broccoli Florettes steamed tender crisp<br>
Sliced green onions<br>
Shredded part skim Mozzarella cheese
</td>
</tr>
</table>

<p>
1. Sprinkle baking sheet with cornmeal.  Roll dough to 8-inch circle; place on baking sheet.  Bake at 425 _ F for 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
 <p>
2. Spread crust with sauce; sprinkle with remaining ingredients.  Return to the oven and bake for 10 minutes or until hot and cheese is bubbly.
 



  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
