</head>

<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 Fettucini with Broccoli and Chicken
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Fettucini with Broccoli and Chicken
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>4-6 Servings</b></nobr><br>
2 oz.	<br>	
1 Tbs.	<br>
1 lb.	<br>
-<br>
1 lb.	<br>
8 oz.	<br>	
-<br>
4 oz.	<br>	
-<br>
3 cups	<br>	
-<br>
1/4 cup	<br>	
-<br>
1 lb.		
</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>50 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	1 1/4 lbs.<br>
1/2 cup	<br>
10 lbs.<br>
-<br>
10 lbs.	<br>
5 lbs.<br>
-<br>
2 1/2 lbs.<br>
-<br>
2 gallons<br>
-<br>
2 1/2 cups<br>
-<br>
10 lbs.
   </td>



   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Butter or margarine<br>
Minced garlic<br>
	Chicken breast, boneless, skinless, sliced 1/2" <br>thick, 
		1 1/2" long<br>
Manns Broccoli Wokly<br>
Fresh mushrooms, medium size, washed, well-<br>
		drained, quartered<br>
Red bell pepper, stemmed and seeded, julienne 
		sliced, 1/8" x 1" long<br>
Alfredo sauce, prepared or purchased, cold, <br>well mixed
<br>
Basil pesto sauce, prepared or purchased, cold, well mixed
<br>
Cooked fettucini noodles, chilled, well drained
   </td>





   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Melt the butter or margarine over medium heat in suitable size skillet.  Do not allow the butter or margarine to brown.<p>
2. Add the minced garlic and chicken strips, stirring to blend evenly with the butter or margarine. Cook the mixture just until the chicken surfaces are white, stirring occasionally to insure uniform heating.<p>
3. Add the Broccoli Wokly, mushrooms and red pepper, blending all ingredients together.  Continue cooking until the broccoli is cooked but still crisp.
<p>4. Add the Alfredo and Pesto sauces, stirring to blend all ingredients.
<p>5. Heat the sauces to a simmer, stirring frequently to prevent scorching or sticking.  Be careful not to overheat sauce, which could separate the oil from the Pesto sauce.
<p>6. When the skilled contents are hot, add the cooked, drained fettucini noodles and blend with the other ingredients.  Continue heating until the pasta is hot.
<p>7. Remove from heat, serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
<p></font><i>Notes:  Large batch preparation may require draining excess liquid from the chicken and vegetables before adding the sauces.  To expedite  cooking, the broccoli can be blanched, "shocked" and drained in advance.  The Pesto sauce can be prepared in advance and held hot until needed.</i>



<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u><pre>
Calories	568
Protein:	40.2 G
Carbohydrate:	46.1 G
Dietary Fiber:	63.4 G
Fat-total:	25.7 G
Cholesterol:	139 mg
Sodium:		1243 mg
  </pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
<a href="../fsrecipesearch.htm">Back to Search Page</a> |
<a href="../fsrecipestoc.htm">Back to Recipe Table of Contents</a>
</center>
