<head>
<title>Mann's Broccoli Food Service Recipes</title>
<!--  created by gvdw on 7/1/96 for Mann's Broccoli  -->
<!--  last edited on 7/30/96 by gavdw  -->
</head>

<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
Broccoli Wokly Individual Veggie Lasagna
</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Broccoli Wokly Individual Veggie Lasagna
</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>8 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
3 cups	<br>	
2 lbs.	<br>
3 1/2 lbs.	<br>
2 lbs.		<br>
1/2 lb.		
</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>50 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	3 1/2 qts.<br>
12 1/2 lbs.	<br>
22 lbs.	<br>
12 1/2 lbs.<br>
3 1/2 lbs.	
   </td>



   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Marinara sauce<br>
Cooked bowtie noodles, well drained<br>
Ratatouille filling, prepared<br>
Low fat cheese filling, prepared<br>
Mozzarella cheese, shredded
   </td>








   </tr>
   </table>
</center>

<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Place 1 oz. of Marinara sauce on the bottom of each individual container.
 <p>
2. Place 2 oz. of chilled noodle evenly over the sauce.
 <p>
3. Place 1/2 cup of prepared Ratatouille filling over the sauce.
 <p>
4. Evenly spread 1/2 cup of cheese mixture over the Ratatouille filling.
 <p>
5. Place 2 additional ounces of cooked noodles over the cheese filling.
 <p>
6. Spread an additional ounce of Marinara sauce over the noodles and top each lasagna with 1 oz. of cheese and refrigerate until needed.
 <p>
7. Bake on a sheet pan for 25-35 minutes at 350 degrees

<p>
<font color="green"><b>Low-Fat Ricotta Cheese Filling<br>
(Ratatouille Filling)</b></font><br>

<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>8 Servings	</b></nobr><br>

2 lbs.	<br>	
1/2 lb.	<br>
2 Tbs.	<br>
1/4 cup	<br>
1 tsp.		
</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>50 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	12 1/2 lbs.<br>
3 1/2 lbs.	<br>
1 cup	<br>
1 1/2 cups	<br>
1 1/2 Tbs.
   </td>



   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Low fat ricotta <br>
Low-moisture mozzarella cheese, shredded<br>
Fresh chopped garlic<br>
Fresh chopped parsley<br>
White pepper, ground
   </td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
1. In a suitable size mixing bow, combine and gently mix all of the above ingredients.  Refrigerate until needed
<p>
<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>8 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
1/2 cup<br>
2 lbs.	<br>	
12 oz.	<br>	
2 lbs.	<br>
2 lbs.	<br>
2 lbs.	<br>
1 lb.	<br>	
2 oz.	<br>
2 qts.	<br>
2 tsp.		


</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>50 Servings</b></nobr><br>
		2 cups	<br>
12 lbs.<br>
4 1/2 lbs.<br>
12 lbs.	<br>
12 lbs.	<br>
12 lbs.<br>
6 lbs.<br>
1 1/2 cups	<br>
2 1/2 gallons	<br>
2 1/2 Tbs.
   </td>
	

   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Vegetable oil<br>
Yellow onions, cut into 1" cubes<br>
Green peppers, seeded, cut into 1" cubes<br>
Eggplant, cut into cubes 1/4" thick<br>
Zucchini, cut into cubes 1/4" thick<br>
	Yellow squash, cut into 1/4" thick<br>
Broccoli Wokly<br>
Fresh chopped garlic<br>
Marinara sauce<br>
Salt
   </td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. In a steam-jacketed kettle or large pot, heat the oil.  Place the onions in the kettle and cook over medium heat for ten minutes, occasionally stirring until onions become transparent.
 <p>
2. Add the green peppers to the kettle or pot, mix well and cook for 5-7 minutes or until peppers are tender.
 <p>
3. Add the eggplant, yellow squash and zucchini to the kettle or pot and gently mix so that all the ingredients cook evenly.  Cook the vegetable mixture for 20 additional minutes.
 <p>
4. Add the Marinara sauce, garlic, salt and pepper to the vegetable mixture and gently stir to incorporate all the ingredients.  Cook for another 10 minutes.
 <p>
5. Place the vegetable mixture in an appropriate storage container and allow to chill before making the lasagna.

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font><pre>
Calories:	744.9
Protein:	34.7 G
Carbohydrate:	80.46 G
Dietary Fiber:	8.25 G
Fat-total:	34.68
Cholesterol:	90.44 mg
Sodium:		2113 mg
  </pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
