<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
 Mangia Mangia Pasta Salad

</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Mangia Mangia Pasta Salad

</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>8-10 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
1 lb.	<br>
3 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
1 lb.	<br>
4 oz.	<br>	
-<br>
8 oz.	<br>
8 oz.	<br>
4 oz.	<br>
3 oz.	<br>
3 cups	
</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>50 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	5 lbs.	<br>
12 lbs.<br>
-<br>
5 lbs.	<br>
1 1/4 lbs.<br>
-<br>
2 1/2 lbs.	<br>
2 1/2 lbs.	<br>
1 1/4 lbs.	<br>

1 lb.	<br>
4 qts.	
   </td>






   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Manns Broccoli Wokly<br>
	Cooked bowtie noodles, chilled and well<br> drained<br>
Cooked chicken breast, cut into julienne strips<br>
Fresh Red Bell Peppers, cut into julienne <br>strips<br>
Yellow squash, cut into 1/4" thick semi circles<br>
Zucchini, cut 1/4" thick semi circles<br>
Green onions, tops only, 1" bias cut<br>
Pine nuts, toasted<br>
Pesto dressing, prepared, chilled </font><i>(see notes below)</i>
   </td>






   </tr>
   </table>
</center>
<font face="Helvetica">
<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Place chicken, cooked noodles and all of the vegetables in a suitable mixing container.  Gently toss the ingredients to thoroughly blend together.
 <p>
2. Pour the dressing over the salad ingredients and gently toss together, evenly and completely coating all the vegetables, chicken and noodles with dressing.
 <p>
3. Allow the salad to chill 1 hour prior to serving.  At the time of service, sprinkle the pine nuts evenly over each salad.
 <p>
<font color="green"><b>TO PREPARE PESTO DRESSING</b><br></font>
1. Using a prepared Creamy Italian Dressing of your choice, prepare the dressing as follows:
 <p>
2. To prepare one quart of dressing, mix 3 cups of Italian Dressing with 1 cup of your favorite prepared basil pesto sauce.
 <p>
3. Blend dressing thoroughly, obtaining a finished dressing of uniform color and consistency.

<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font></font><pre>
Calories:	604
Protein:	25.1 G
Carbohydrate:	39.7 G
Dietary Fiber:	5.35 G
Fat-total:	46.6 G
Cholesterol:	72.3 mg
Sodium:		616 mg
 </pre>
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
