<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
  MANNS Brocco Burrisimo&#153;

</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Brocco Burrisimo&#153;

</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>48 Servings	</b></nobr><br>
7 1/2 lbs.	<br>	
4 1/2 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
4 1/2 lbs.	<br>	
1 1/2 lbs.	<br>
6 lbs.	<br>
4 dozen	<br>
1 1/2 lbs.	

</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>96 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	15 lbs.<br>
9 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
9 lbs.<br>
3 lbs.	<br>
12 lbs.	<br>
8 dozen	<br>
3 lbs.	

   </td>



   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Prepared mild salsa<br>
Manns Pizza-cut Broccoli Florettes,<br>
		steamed crisp-tender<br>
Drained, canned pinto beans<br>
Drained, canned corn kernels<br>
Hot, cooked white rice<br>
Warm, flour tortillas, 10"<br>
Shredded cheddar cheese
   </td>





   </tr>
   </table>
</center>
<font face="Helvetica">
<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Place the salsa, broccoli florettes, beans and corn in a large pot; heat through.  Mixture may be held on a steam table.
 <p>
2. For each serving:  Place 2 oz. rice down the center of 1 tortilla.  Top with 6 oz. broccoli mixture and 1/2 ounces cheese.  Roll up and serve.




<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font></font><pre>
Calories:	311.5
Protein:	10.62 G
Carbohydrate:	50.61 G
Dietary Fiber:	2.67 G
Fat-total:	7.01 G
Cholesterol:	16.88 mg
Sodium:		1136 mg
 </pre>

<i>Brocco Burrisimo is a trademark of Mann Packing Company, Inc.</i>
 
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
