<!---------------------------End Keywords----------------------->


<body text="#000000" vlink="green" link="#6A006A" bgcolor="#FFEBD7"><center>
<font face="Helvetica" size="7" color="#6A006A">
  Brocco Taco&#153;


</font>

<table width="600" border="0">
<tr>
<td>

  


<!----------------#2------------------------>
  <table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" bordercolor="#808040" cellpadding="7">
  <tr>
  <td><font face="Helvetica">
<center>
   <table cellspacing="12" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
   <tr>
   <td colspan="3">
<font face="Helvetica" color="green"><b>
MANNS Brocco Taco&#153;

</b></font>
   </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>

<p>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>48 Servings	</b></nobr><br>

6 lbs.	<br>	
6 lbs.<br>	
3 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
3 lbs.	<br>
8 dozen		<br>
3 lbs.	<br>
1 1/2 lbs.	

</td>
<td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
	<nobr><b>96 Servings</b></nobr><br>
	12 lbs.<br>
12 lbs.	<br>
6 lbs.	<br>
-<br>
6 lbs.	<br>
16 dozen<br>
6 lbs.	<br>
3 lbs.
   </td>
	

   <td valign="top"><font face="Helvetica">
<b>Ingredients</b><br>
Prepared mild salsa<br>
Drained, canned pinto beans<br>
Manns Pizza-cut Broccoli Florettes, <br>
		steamed crisp-tender<br>
Diced tomatoes<br>
Warm ,prepared taco shells<br>
Manns Broccoli Cole Slaw<br>
Shredded Cheddar Cheese
   </td>




   </tr>
   </table>
</center>
<font face="Helvetica">
<p>

<b>PROCEDURE:</b><br>
1. Place the salsa, beans, broccoli florettes an tomatoes in a large pot; heat through.  Mixture may be held on a steam table.
 <p>
2. For each serving:  Line 2 taco shells each with 1/2 ounce broccoli cole slaw.  Top each with 3 ounces bean mixture and 1/4 oz. cheese.




<p>
<u><b>Nutrients Per Serving</b></u></font></font><pre>
Calories:	266
Fat-total:	10.46 G
Protein:	8.65 G
Cholesterol:	18.46 mg
Carbohydrate:	34.53 G
Sodium:		1033 mg
Dietary Fiber:	2.72 G
 </pre>

<i>Brocco Taco is a trademark of Mann Packing Company, Inc.</i>
 
  </td>
  </tr>
  </table>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
