<html>
<head>

<CENTER><title>Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease</title></CENTER>
 </head>
<CENTER><H3>Fundraising and Support for CJD Victims</H3></CENTER>
<CENTER> <I>Please also see scientific and medical journal articles<P></I></CENTER>
<HR>

 The   Creutzfeldt-Jakob   Disease   Foundation  can  provide  more
information on this malady. The foundation intends to have a Web site on the Internet. It can be reached at:<P>
Creutzfeldt-Jakob   Disease   Foundation<BR>

      P.O. Box 611625<BR>

      Miami, Fla. 33261-1625<BR>

      <HR>

<p> The <B>Creutzfeldt-Jakob Support Group</B> offers support to victims' families and is the only organisation campaigning for urgent research into the disease.<P>

ALL of us feel sympathy for those whose livelihoods have been seriously damaged by the BSE crisis. However, financial aid for the meat industry will run to billions of pounds yet only 4.5 million has been pledged for research into CJD, despite the possibility that unknown numbers of people may be afflicted by this appalling condition.
<p> Please support us by sending donations made out to the Creutzfeldt-Jakob Network and by lobbying your MP and Euro MP to press for funding for research.
<p>M TREADWELL (Mrs), Fund-raising co-ordinator, Creutzfeldt-Jakob Support Network, 98 Milton Mill Lane, High Milton, Doncaster DN5 7TF....<FONT SIZE=-1><FONT SIZE=-1> BY ALAN HAMILTON</FONT></FONT>
<HR>
<B>Getting Help</B><P>
With the rise of BSE and the increase in CJD incidence, it was thought that more money would be derived from charity. So far this has not taken place. UK government has made it plain that an increase in funding would give the impression that there was a risk to humans.<P>

1) <a href="http://www.airtime.co.uk/bse/char.htm">Charities associated with BSE</a><p><UL>

<LI>The Spongiform Encephalopathy Research Campaign...<P>
<LI>The Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease Support Network<p><LI>The Alzheimer's Disease Society (Because of the similarity of the two conditions the society also supports CJD work.) <BR>

</UL>

2) <a href="http://www.va.gov/publ/direc/health/195076.htm">
 Management of patients </a>identified in the CREUTZFELDT JAKOB Disease lookback.
<p>

3) <a href="http://www.lm.com/~nab/neurodis.html">Disease Information: </a> A Long Good-Bye - Reflections on Dealing with Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease.
<HR>
<H3>British vegetarian information phone line</H3>

IN LIGHT of the continuing confusion and conflicting reports and information concerning BSE, readers may like to know that the vegetarian charity Viva! has launched a BSE helpline - tel 01270 522500 (weekdays 10am-7pm).
<p> Viva! will supply free information listing foods containing beef products and ideas for safe alternatives. You can also write to them at Viva! PO Box 212, Crewe CW1 4SD.
<p>J ISHERWOOD, Avondale Road, Darwen.
<HR>


</body>
